(27845, ' [quote=KageFox]While on the topic of sights, is there any way to improve the iron sights on the TT??? Just wondering....[/quote]\n\nI have a mak, I love the gun but sights suck...both Mak and TT have very small fronth sight which is fixed protrusion from the slide. You can not replace the fronth sight. There are two ways to improve it\nHave an experienced gunsmith cut-off the fronth sight.\nCut out a notch to fit a sight (you have to decide and buy the sights prior to this)\nAdjust the rear notch cut for the rear sight base.\nFit the sights\nsight them in (you may use bore sighter for this purpose)\nGo to the range and do the fine tuning at 25 meters.\n\nThis whole process is going to cost more than your TT.\n\nSecond option is to have an expert smith weld on to the fronth sight some softer material to increase its size, carefully file it to shape. this can be accomplished cheaply and easily.', ''),
