(27920, ' My Frinds... I have personally experienced the thing as i carry the weapon in my car .. let it be 144 or not. As the 144 permit is only a misguided letter which says that you are allowed to carry a weapon but when 144 is imposed you cannot. \nThe original 144 carry permits are issued for a certain period i.e. when the sec.144 is imposed you apply for the permit and you can carry the weapon till the time of 144. One the time lapses the permit is also lapsed. Even if the govt. extends the 144 (they have to issue new order after 24 hrs) the permit is deeemed cancelled and one has to apply for a new one.', ''),
(27922, ' The information stated above is based on my experience as I once got the permit issued through home department and then I know that its just a gimmick. The agents will charge you Rs.1000 whereas its just a letter which if one has contacts can be issued for free. \n\nplease dont take my words for granted as nowadays the terrorism situation is so much hyped that even police and other law enforcement agencies can raise eyebrows on legal issues. the best thing is to avoid circumstance where you are vunerable in eyes of law. \n\nAprt from this the Law regarding the licensed weapons also stated that the law officer can even get your weapon confiscate a weapon and can arrest a person even if the license is present... for this the officer had just to show his doubt on the person.', ''),
