(28099, ' [quote=hasanjamshad]@12Gauge, Sir no doubt IZMASH is a good company much better than the TURKISH, but if we compare it with the other EUROPEAN giants like PERRAZI(that historically win more than 40% medals in skeet & trap competitions) and BERETTA(that wins 31% medals in skeet and trap competitions) will be too much streching. Baikal has a history of wininig around 7% medals.\nThe world record that we are talking about is just the extraordinary talent of Mr YURI TSURANOV not the extraordinary performance of MTs6(the model that he used to use in competitions). I tried a lot but wasn''t able to find a single western european medal winner who used a BAIKAL. Sir, if there are some BAIKAL users in europe they must be doing so in their early carrier when they couldn''t afford an expensive gun.[/quote]\n\n\nSir!, u got it all wrong, its not my intention to compare Baikal vs perazzi/beretta/kreigoff. i''m only comparing a budget gun with another budget gun (Russian vs Turkish). comparing baikal to a london best or itanlian best was never my intention.\n\nallow me to post the original question:\n\n[quote]Dear fellows want to buy an overunder shotgun with in the range of 40000 K to 50000K....please advise whichone to go for and where can i go to buy it being in Islamabad/Rawalpindi.\n[/quote]\n\nnow u know why i''m comparing Baikal to a Turkish. :)\nhint: look at the budget range. hint2: i''m only comparing two budget guns. hint3: pointless to compare to a high end english/italian/american o/u, being out of budget range.\n\nRegards.', ''),
