(28135, ' [quote]1- Darra made guns are no where close to Turkish guns.[/quote]\n\nmarey bhai, marey bhai, i never said turkish guns are close to darra made guns in quality, i merely suggested that turkish shotgun manufacturing industry is similar to darra but only equipped with more sophisticated machinery and hence are able to produce products of a far higher quality then darra guns. (remember i even mentioned CNC machinery)\n\nallow me to explain:\n\nturkish gun manufacturing industry works using the cluster style (execuse the missing techinical term, as i''m no technical person) of manufacturing where one person (of the same industry) makes barrels and other makes other specialized parts. the big names that u hear or read about are basically assembler who just assemble those part and stamp their names on it. sort of like Pakistan''s dawlance and sabro type industries. they just order the parts from manufacturers and assemble/stamp/package/market the final product under their name.\n\n[quote]5-In Beijing one Russian won a bronze but he was shooting with PERAZZI(ALIPOVE ALEXY).[/quote]\n\nI know, i never said, if u could afford a perazzi buy a baikal, i merely suggested that if u gotta choose a cheaper shotgun go for baikal.\n\nRegards.\n\np.s. i''m now searching for a magazine i got in my house on russian civilian arms industry where it explicitly says that TSKB orders guns from IMZ and then how those guns are customized. it even said how extensively TSBK invests in getting those guns pattersn statistically tested. and yes TSKB are not exported to any country direct from the factory. a second hand might find its way to other countries, but a new one is a rare thing indeed.\n\none more thing brother: in the end, this debate is all about Russian vs Turkish. in my opinion and experience, Russians are the best in budget catagory, hey, if i could afford a london best, i would drop baikal in a heart beat.', ''),
