(28250, ' [quote=12gauge]\n\nBluff, buddy, do lemme know how come u can buy of these guns in a budget range of 40-50K. cause i sure would like to buy some ov them. by the way, i very much doubt it that anybody would recommend a 4 lbs gun for skeet/trap.\n\nits strange, u say a recommended skeet gun shoud be around 8lbs and yet its on top of the list u''ve given. however i''m happy to see that u''ve listed Baikal in the middle of the list amongst browning, franchi, rizzini.\n\nu know there is a saying: if u gotta lose, atleast lose from the very best.\n\nthats my original point: Baikal/Russian guns are the very best budget guns in the world. lemme reiterate, very best budget guns in the world.\n\nRegards.[/quote]\n1. yes baikal is in the middel of the list but not 12guage, its 20 guage..... due to its lesser weight.(weight was the actual point of confusion)\n \n2. i never asked snmailk (who started the thread)to buy any gun which i mentioned in my list (that list was only to tell you that light weight guns are mostly recomended for skeets and trap)\n\n3. i am telling you again and again " the choice of gun is very personal ".... but to me IZH 27 12 guage is not a practical  skeet gun.', ''),
