(28255, ' I never compared RUSSIAN BAIKAL with EUROPEAN BEST as that was beyond the scope of this thread. Brother, i just tried to straighten few facts that were far from reality. Discussion was regarding BAIKAL vs TURKISH shotguns. Nodoubt BAIKALs are better choice but there are some imaginative facts about the BAIKALS in some of your previous posts. I just tried to correct those facts just to provide a true information to our fellow members. Some of them really think that we know more. \n\n[quote]12gauge wrote:\n\nTurkish shotguns are nothing but a well organized equivalent of our Darra. [/quote]\n\nWhen i showed reservations over DARRA vs TURKISH, i was responding to your this stance. Now you have given some respect to TURKISH shotguns that was basically my intention as i mentioned earlier that they have better manufecturing facilities, machines and metallurgy. Definitely Beretta didn,t establish a new plant in the name of Stoeger but bought an existing plant named(VURSAN, this plant used to manufecture clones of BENELLI, really good clones).\n\n[quote]12gauge wrote:\n\nkreigoff, beretta and browning were at top three with around 20 percent each and the fourth largest catagory was Baikal at around 8 to 12 percent[/quote]\n\nSir, when i posted some facts about the PERAZZI and BERETTA i never intended to compare BAIKAL with these EUROPEAN wonders but just wanted to correct the record as you never mentioned the best performer PERAZZI(won 11 medals in beijing out of total 15 and 8 in 2004). At the same time KREIGHOFF and BROWNING are not that good performers in international competitions.\n\n[quote]12GAUGE wrote:\n\nTSKIB, made russia win olympic skeet 4 times in a row. and the gun was baikal IZH27.[/quote]\n\nSir, IZH27 is not the gun that Russian shooters use but is MTs 6 and its varients. These MTs are never made by IZHMASH but by KBP that is a different company and much prestigeous company. They don''t make cheap stuff like Baikal but very fine and expensive stuff. We can compare it with London best or European best. At the same time for our fellow members Russia never bagged 4 olympic golds is a row nor it won four golds in skeet in the history of Olympic Skeet. Yes, in the 1968 olympics PETROVE won a gold in skeet and that is the only gold they have in this decipline. Petrove and Yuri TSURANOV showed some extraordinary skills of markesmanship in the comming years.\n\nI am posting a link just to have a fair idea about the IZH and the MTs. This is not cheap stuff by BAIKAL but something special, that more expensive than BERETTAs etc.\n[url]http://www.shotgunworld.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=124415[/url]\n\nSir, Baikal doesn''t need imaginative work to win over a Turkish gun. This must clarefy the expression that you got about my posts.  \n\nBest Regards:', ''),
