(28308, ' @12guage.... bro i saw one TOZ 120 with Haji Amin (international arms Islamabad ) asking is 45 K for it with silver receiver , fixed chocks, light weight.\ni have toz 120 with variable chocks bought a year back .... and my father has tula semiauto .... well you ll find tula (both O/U and Semi )equivelant to any good europian standard gun,  its pattern is pritty much like browning and winchester.. \nOne of our fellow member (talal Khan) used to have toz 120 , and he talked loud for it. \none thing which i felt in toz (O/U and Semi ) is there performance with full chocks.... that it make a lose patteren than IZH with full chocks at 35-40 yds...... (like all turkish shotguns). Finish is same like all russain shotguns.\nOverall TOZ 120  a very practicle gun.... go for it if u want a to increase ur collection or want secondry gun ur closet for hunting and sporting.', ''),
(28309, ' @Aamar .... you are right about the procedure. But keep i mind licenses issued by Sindh government at the moment will not be made All Pakistan immediately. You will have to wait for 1 year then only they can make it All Pakistan. \nBut considering the loopholes ... you can get it done through some agent who will charge you and extra 2000 apart from the original fee of Rs. 2000.\n[quote=Aamar][quote=Acciprone]@Ameem\n\nI think the important question here is it equal to MOI.  I think not. It is extended to all PAK yes.. but any changes in local law would affect the licence but MOI liecnes dont get affected. \n\nany other member has more knowledge on this .. pls share[/quote]\n\nI would be very wary of the Lasbella license, the "Extended to all Pakistan" can only be done at the Home Secretary''s Personal Discretion , have the license checked out at both the issuing DCO and Karachi DCO offices and the home department for the "All Pakistan"\n\nBut, if your source is "reliable", then it should be on the level .......\n\nAlso, once, the "All Pakistan" status is given to a provincial license then there is no REAL difference from a MOI license ..... The annual fee may vary but that''s it :)[/quote]', ''),
