(28312, ' @Abbas you are right abut this as the same thing happened to a friend of mine and the DCO asked for all types of documents. But once we went there in person he only asked to see the original ID card. Upon our inquiry he told us that many licenses of PB have been issued without proper documentation and procedures ... thus they take application and all necessary documents so if anything goes wrong they will have a proper record with them.\n\nNo idea how far this statement of DCO is justified but that''s the procedure that we followed.\n\n[quote=Abbas]Yesterday I sent someone to give my licenses for entry to the DC office and they sent him back saying that they require.\n\n1). Original License\n2). Original ''Gift'' recipt in case if P.B weapon\n3). Original NIC\n4). Copy of NIC\n5). Application made out to the DCO to enter the weapon signed by the applicant\n\nStrange and complicated, just last week you could register with only a receipt from the shop and the original license.[/quote]', ''),
(28313, ' [quote=Abbas]Yesterday I sent someone to give my licenses for entry to the DC office and they sent him back saying that they require.\n\n1). Original License\n2). Original ''Gift'' recipt in case if P.B weapon\n3). Original NIC\n4). Copy of NIC\n5). Application made out to the DCO to enter the weapon signed by the applicant\n\nStrange and complicated, just last week you could register with only a receipt from the shop and the original license.[/quote]\n\n\nI sent my npb to have it entered to the DCO all they required was the copy of niic /copy of licence and the original purchase recipt and 500 Rs. gave it 11am got it at 4pm', ''),
