(28410, ' 12 Guage.. have U ever had any experience with a seiga 12?\n\nnone whatsoever. wish i could but my pocket (in other words my wife) doesnt allow me to experience this very last stage of evolution of a shotgun. :(\n\nif i ever did manage to get one. i''ll die peacefully and my tombstone will say: "a good son, a good brother, a good husband, a good father and he F*****g owned a saiga12K.\n\nor " I''ve lived, I''ve loved, I''ve pumped and damn! I had a saiga12K too"\n\n[quote]Have u seen the latest Baikal semi in synthetic with optima (type) chokes ????\n\nIf yes, how is it different from older models and whats the price tag ?\n[/quote]\n\nI think by optima, u''r talking about extended chokes, yes, I have used them. if u use steel they are great, if u use lead, they are not worth a damn thing. in my experience, baikal''s flush mounted chokes pattern better than extended.\n\nbesides, extended chokes have nothing to do with the model or year of make. infact, i see newer models comming with flush mounted chokes only, older ones i''ve seen were supplied ocassionaly with extended chokes.\n\nRegards.', ''),
