(28525, ' Nothing beats a diana, but if you are looking for a hunting style airgun with plenty of power, you can''t go wrong with a .22 Gamo Hunter 440 or a Shadow 1000. I myself got a Shadow 1000 last year for Rs 16K. Polymer body, lightweight, fairly powerful, manageable recoil. Works beautifully with Pro Magnum pellets. However, this is not, repeat not, a target rifle. Though it is accurate at the regular airgun ranges, just don''t expect it to put 10 pellets in the 10-ring everytime at 10m. A funny coincidence, but I feel that my particular airgun is more accurate on objects rather than targets :D\n\nPS. Diana is too expensive for an airgun.', ''),
