(28561, ' [b]Hunting arms manufacturers to visit Turkey\nSaturday, June 06, 2009\nThe News.[/b]\n\nPESHAWAR: Pakistan Hunting and Sporting Arms Development Company (PHSADC) is sending a delegation of small arms manufacturers to Turkey with the objective of improvement in production standards of non-lethal weapons through transfer of technology.\n\nIn a press release, PHSADC Chairman Nauman Wazir said that they were sending arms manufacturers so that they could have knowledge about new technology and advancement in gun manufacturing and could replicate modern techniques in the country.\n\nThe delegation, comprising six members, would leave on June 11 and will return after six days. During the visit, Wazir added, the delegation members would hold meetings with different gun manufacturers and engineers besides holding discussions with heads of government departments regulating arms production in Turkey.\n\nHe said gun manufacturing technology is very latest and advanced in Turkey and the PHSADC realised this during an international exhibition of arms held recently in Germany.\n\nHe said production standards, value addition of products and finishing are very fine in Turkey and the PHSADC wants to get information about the technology and its replication in Pakistan.\n\n“Without improving production standards and value addition of products, we cannot attract foreign buyers for hunting and sporting arms being produced in Pakistan,” he said.\n\nWazir said the company has been set up with the objective of harnessing the untapped potential of gun manufacturing in Pakistan. The PHSADC, he continued, is striving to increase export of hunting and sporting arms manufactured in Pakistan by developing and enhancing skills and craftsmanship of gunsmiths.', ''),
