(28739, ' Fantastic GTG ! It was great meeting everyone again and some members for the first time as well.\n\nThe gtg was divided into three sessions (four for me). The small arms range, skeet/trap, dinner at Lal Qila and a full fledged hunt arranged for me by Imu10. \n\nThank you all the Karachi members for making me feel so at home, it was great to meet you all. \n\nA special thanks to Taurus and IMU10 for arranging and coordinating everything so effortlessly which in turn ran very smoothly. Taurus is indeed a true PakGunner at heart and a great person. I''m happy to count him among my close friends.\n\nAnd a special mention for Bloodbath, +10 to you, all of us were very impressed with your manner, personality and care for other members. You are indeed one of our most valued new members. Hope to see and interact a lot more with you in the future InshAllah.\n\nI request Sohail and Imu10 to team up with Bloodbath for helping our members better their shooting scores and for teaching members proper procedural gun safety.\n\n@Shariq I will not meet you next time and you know why ! :P\n\n@Sohail, Acciprone, Thunder, OHQ, Striker1, Cap1, Memon, Maverick, Moin Sahib, Rehan, Bullseye, ARK Tareen, ChocTalpur, OmKhan, 9mm It was absolutely great seeing you all (again) and InshAllah hope to spend more time with you all in coming trips.', ''),
(28740, ' [quote=Abbas]4 bores in 7 shots right Imu10 ? :cool: One injured as well.[/quote]\n\nNice work Abbas for finding the map of saeed pur (tando mohammad khan district)\nlol! yes abbas it was 7 shots and 4 wildboars and one injured as well which could be in your bag very easily with the help of those hunting ferocious dogs But.....................\nguys it was an amazing trip a very short one we got lots of pictures and movies for all you guys,i hope u all will like the pics and could feel the "fun in the sun" which we had \nthe hunt was amazing, as it was too hot and the drive was aproximately of 2.5hours to saeed pur  but abbas sitting right next to me we just talked and talked and talked as i already told abbas in advance that "TRUST ME IT WOULD BE A ONCE IN A LIFE TIME EXPERIENCE".\nI am so happy that abbas liked the trip and am sure all his tiredness is gone after shooting a wildboar with a steyr professional .270 calibre [b](i know this tour to karachi GTG was most expensive for abbas coz i know after yesterdays shoot at skeet range and todays shoot of bolt action rifle Abbas can''t keep his hands off these two  new toys any more for long)[/b]\n\nand in the last i really would like to thank abbas for coming with me and joining me for a Wildboar Hunt', ''),
(28743, ' its a great piece , love it congrats.', ''),
(28744, ' Really nice friends, congrats for arranging such a marvelous party. +1 to Hamid i think we shouldn''t waste time and arrange a GTG in LAHORE. I would love to be the host.', ''),
(28745, ' Wow!! Guys it was such a nice GTG and such a big attendance of our very own Pak Gunners as our chief guest was here all the way from lahore just to attend the GTG held in karachi\nand A BIG THANKS to OHQ(omar hamza qureshi) as well  cjoining us for the GTG and for being such a nice and wonderfull person,\ni am so very happy that abbas really liked what ever we collectively did for the GTG and the dinner at lalQila. \ni would like to congratulate Taurus for all his efforts and the amount of time he gave to make this GTG so memorable, he was the face behind the success and smooth going of this GTG and keeping abbas occupied with a lovely company of his \nThunder once again you have taken some amazing pics,which was exactly expected from you and you did justice being the photjournalist of pakguns\n"OVER ALL THE GTG WAS AN UNFORGETTABLE ONE AND THIS GTG HAS SET THE BAR HIGH, FOR THE FUTURE GTG''S"', ''),
