(28982, ' @ Bluff\n\nYou may not hunt. Others will. These bans have nothing to do with save wildlife. These are all ploys by the pimps of the foreigners to get more money out of their masters. They go and claim to them that they have banned hunting so that their is more game for them (the foreign masters who wear white cushion covers and table cloths), and in return they get more money for their "conservation efforts".\n\nIt is good to be law abiding, but not at the expense of one''s own rights. What lies on the land, below it, above it, and on and in the waters on that land, is the inalienable birth right of the sons and daughters of that soil. Deny it, and you will have insurgencies and rebellions. You needn''t go far, look whats happening in Balochistan.', ''),
