(28994, ' I have owned Winchester Super-X 3! It fires really fast and has a record of firing 12 rounds in under 1.5 second! But kind of shooting I remain or should I say we remain involved in doesn''t require such repeating fire powe! We hardly get a chance to shoot such zoooming birds! Partridges, Quails, Ducks require a normal shotgun/semi-auto that can handle the situation. Buying Winchester Super-X 3 was an impulsive decision and later I regreted it! THAT''S MY PERSONAL EXPERIENCE! I did not like the gun...it was designed good had the ability to shoot fast but to me it appeared to be little lousy! Extrema-2 is for serious water fowlers and suites those who sit and shoot! You can not take it on walk up shoots because of its weight. But if you are into serious water fowling then that is the gun! For SD and HD purposes there are lots of variants available in th market and every shotgun has its own features but altogather all appear to have same mechanism & purpose i.e. HD & SD.\nOther then that if you want to know about the best shotguns of the world then try followings:\n\n[url]http://www.thefield.co.uk/features/153911/The_world039s_20_best_shotguns.html#link[/url]\n\n[url]http://money.cnn.com/galleries/2008/fortune/0801/gallery.collectorguns.fortune//index.html[/url]\n\nThese two links would take you to the list of guns that are considered to be\nTOP IN QUALITY/CRAFTSMANSHIP/PERFORMANCE/WORTH ;)', ''),
