(29129, ' [quote]Finally, sir, please explain "Since you found it in wilderness it''s not a crime as bad as poaching". Thank you.[/quote]\n\nLol ... I meant in the eyes of any wild life department (not Pakistan) this is a smaller crime as compared to poaching because whether you found them in wilderness or you poach ... once they discover these horns from you they won''t spare you but if ultimately proved that it was not poaching and you found them in wilderness, perhaps, they would let you go ... But you made a big mistake by giving them to the wild life department in Pakistan, although, it was a good job you did and we all must appreciate it but do you think they will register it in their syndicate ... No Way ... they must have gifted them to one of their senior beaurocrats or some high ranking politician or some wadera ..etc \n\nNext time ... keep it as your own trophy because you found it !', ''),
