(29286, ' [quote=Bluff]:) 12 guage... bhai actually the guns shown in the web link is "max upgraded gun"... like it actually comes with 4+1 but  in the link they have shown 7+1 just to show the possibilty of extention . or you can say the pic shows the rail but in actual even when you buy a NIB you never get rail, infact the pic show you the allowed after market modifications   \nNow they (baikal inc) allow you to buy after market accessories like rail, tubes, mags etc. \nMine was also NIB but without accessories.\n\nDont worry ....merey bhai.[/quote]\n\n\nso very kind of you for the encouraging response however i''m still kinda nervy cause even though the manual and box quotes the serial number and practical shooting model, the gun''s receiver doesnt say practical model, it just lists serial and baikal mp153.\n\ndo u have "practical shooting" model as well? if so, then u''r manual should say practical shooting model as well. and can u please check what accessories were provided with u''r gun, there is a list in the manual, every item provided is clearly marked/checked.\n\nmy checklist (every item was provided, none missing)\n\n1. five flush chokes (C, IC, M, IM, F)\n2. two extended chokes (IC, IM) steel shot only\n3. fiberoptic bead (replacement bead as well)\n4. perspex stock spacer to increase the length of pull\n5. Rubber housing for cocking lever (supposed to make cocking comfortable for the finger)\n6. magazine plug, reduces the cartridge capacity to 2+1\n7. magazine extension (adds just one extra cartridge, absolutely useless)\n8. extra recoil spring (found bent/out of shape)\n9. trigger lock (cheap plastic, broken from the very start)\n10. wrench (for chokes and gas adjustment valve)\n\nRegards.', ''),
