(29436, ' With all the due respect Kaiser bhai, this is a bit too much ... \n\nFirst of all, the Arabs don''t hunt with Goshawks, as it pursuits the Houbara for a certain distance, and then eventually let it go(if the houbara is off its reach i.e.). \nThey do it with Falcons, as the falcon''s moto in houbara hunt is JAAN JAE PER TALOOR NA JAE. The pursuit can go as long as 8-10 kms. \n\nDoosri baat, when they could get a Falcon as good as a Peregrine or even Saker, for as much as Rs. 1-1.5 million these days, why would a person who''s running a state like Dubai, the principal architect of UAE, would invest so much money in something not much of a use to himself woh bhi two decades back.', ''),
