(29438, ' Bluff bhai, i get u''r explaination but here my shotgun differs from u''r explaination.\n\n1. the manual and box of my shotgun says: [b]"MP-153 PRACTICAL SHOOTING" 12/76 SEMI-AUTOMATIC SHOTGUN[/b]\n2. receiver and barrel just say "MP-153"\n3. i''ve got a total of seven chokes (five flush fitting and two extended)\n4. synthetic/polymer furniture (color=black)\n\nall this has lead me be to believe that my gun is actually "a practical shooting model" however when i see the website, there is no mentioning of seven chokes, no mentioning of fiberoptic bead, and hunting and sporting version isnt mentioned there as well.\n\nonly two versions/models are available:\n\n1. baikal mp153\n2. baikal mp153 "practical shooting"\n\nmy greatest concern at this points is the receiver where it doesnt say "practical shooting" and differences in the listed accessories provided and posted on the compay''s website.\n\nRegards.\n\np.s. it could be just my paranoia but i wanted to make sure. I however i must say that i got some cool accessories that arent listed on the company''s website, such as extra recoil spring, fiberoptic bead, extended chokes and stuff.', ''),
