(29588, ' @Psycho Why must every ordinary discussion have to turn into a conspiracy theory ?? One of my reasons for wanting to go in the background is that some people at our site are extremely nosy and try to dig up dirt from every little corner even if it is not there. Your enthusiasm for FP is noted, I''m sure he''s very fond of you as well. :)\n\n+1 to Acciprone and Sohail.\n\nThat being said. Everyone has commitments and preferences. Those that know us personally understand that we have a lot on our plate apart from PakGuns. When I said ''retire'' I did not mean that I would be leaving the site for good, PakGuns is my home, rather I meant that I have cared for and nourished this baby into something that is able to stand on it''s own feet now MashAllah.  What I am doing is wanting to share it with you members, my friends. We will always be in the background monitoring everything including mods. If someone does not come up to the standards expected from them they will be relived of Moderatorship and another member appointed.\n\nOn a very serious note to all members. I am sick and tired of petty forum politics and the trouble makers that come to this site just to get some cheap kicks out of making foolish comments. I have kept a very easy going attitude all this time, however in the future anyone trying to make trouble, indulge in forum politics or dig up dirt etc will find himself instantly banned. We are a firearms enthusiasts site and the purpose for our existence is to discuss our hobby of firearms, please stick to it.\n\nAlso I am well aware that banned members from PakGuns who have nothing else to do with their time browse the forum as guests and then proceed to call everyone they have numbers of to pump them with misinformation and crap. All I can say is, it''s cheap and reflects the level of the persons involved. \n\nNow as for the new mods. One moderator will be appointed from Karachi for sure. Whoever the person is will have to take this job very seriously and follow the exact guidelines laid out for moderation. My personal relations with that member are not important, what is important is that he should be appropriate for PakGuns and will be able to give it his undivided attention. Whatever choice I make I request and expect everyone to endorse as no one as more interest in PakGuns than I. \n\nOn a final note about FP. Currently he is in his village which has limited Internet facility hence his lack of comments even at the Karachi GTG and the Sindh Hunting pictures. PakGuns is his home as much as it is mine and is always open for him. Whenever he is able and feels like participating in a conversation he will. \n\n[b]@All trouble makers and dirt diggers. Consider this a final formal warning. No more bullshit will be tolerated ![/b]', ''),
