(29944, ' And to not forget the MAMMALS ;) The following list includes all mammals which occur in Pakistan and are rated as Critically Endangered (CR), Endangered (EN) or Vulnerable (VU) in the 2005 IUCN Red List of Threatened Animals.  \n\n[b]Endangered:[/b] \n1. Blue Whale (Balaenoptera musculus). \n2. Fin Whale (Balaenoptera physalus). \n3. Hotson''s Mouse-like Hamster (Calomyscus hotsoni). (Endemic to Pakistan.) \n4. Indus River Dolphin (Platanista gangetica minor). \n5. Markhor (Capra falconeri). \n6. Snow Leopard (Uncia uncia). \n7. Woolly Flying Squirrel (Eupetaurus cinereus). \n[b]Vulnerable:[/b] \n1. Argali (Ovis ammon).  \n2. Asiatic Black Bear (Ursus thibetanus). \n3. Blackbuck (Antilope cervicapra). \n4. Dugong (Dugong dugon).  \n5. Eurasian Otter (Lutra lutra).  \n6. Fishing Cat (Prionailurus viverrinus). \n7. Geoffroy''s Bat (Myotis emarginatus).  \n8. Humpback Whale (Megaptera novaeangliae). \n9. Lesser Horseshoe Bat (Rhinolophus hipposideros).  \n10. Mediterranean Horseshoe Bat (Rhinolophus euryale).  \n11. Mouflon (or Urial) (Ovis orientalis). \n12. Sind Bat (Eptesicus nasutus). \n13. Smooth-coated Otter (Lutrogale perspicillata).  \n14. Wild Goat (Capra aegagrus). \n\nHope togather this information is enough to clarify', ''),
