(29989, ' Guns and safety go together.\nA first aid kit is a collection of supplies and equipment for use in giving first aid.First aid kits may be made up of different contents dependant on who has assembled the kit and for what purpose.\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/image.php?v=PqrF_pS][img]http://img3.imageshack.us/img3/3927/96216511.th.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n\nTypical contents include adhesive bandages, regular strength pain medication, gauze and low grade disinfectant.\nSaline for cleaning wounds or washing out foreign bodies from eyes.\nSoap - used with water to clean superficial wounds once bleeding is stopped.\nAntiseptic wipes or sprays for reducing the risk of infection in abrasions or around wounds. Dirty wounds must still be cleaned for antiseptics to be effective. \nI will recommend to have a small bag of following items.\n1)Lighter, for sterilizing tweezers or pliers etc \n2)Painkillers.\n3)Paracetamol.\n4)Anti diarrhea medication.\n5)Antihistamine.\n6)Sticker Bandages.\n7)Disperen.\n8)Water Purification Tablets.\n9)Small Torch.\nWhat kind of First Aid kit you carry while on a shooting range or on Hunting?\nViews are wellcomed.\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/image.php?v=PqrGenJ][img]http://img3.imageshack.us/img3/4588/22646584.th.jpg[/img][/url]', ''),
