(30020, ' I dont have a proper first aid kit but i do carry some stuff recommended by a doctor friend of mine who is in the army. here it goes: (kindly execuse my spelling mistakes as the medical jargon is just beyond me)\n\n1. gauss\n2. duct tape (u''ll be amazed by the things u can do with duct tape)\n3. cotton\n4. medical/doctor''s alcohol\n5. paracetamol\n6. ibro-brufen\n7. antihistamine (its basically an anti-allergic but in injection form for quick relief)\n8. Injection\n9. water purification tablets\n10. sunny plast\n11. lighter with built-in torch\n12. large and strong nilon shoe lace (for snake bite treatment)\n13. a blade (for snake bite treatment)\n14. Septron DS in powdered form (to prevent infection in an open wound)\n15. anti-allergy tablets\n\nsome additional stuff for the super paranoid and incase a practicing doctor accompanies you:\n\n16. medical morphene (for quick pain relief)\n17. adrenaline+injection (to prevent shock and boost body''s strength incase of any severe accident)\n18. defibrillator (it zaps the heart with a jolt of electricity, purpose is to bring the hearts eratic beat back into rythm)\n\nabove three (16, 17 and 18) I dont have but my friend only recommended them incase a practicing doctor joins me for a hunt.\n\nRegards.', ''),
