(30043, ' Here is a photograph of Pakistan''s last real eagle falconer and my late friend, Noorullah Khan Achakzai with his golden eagle. Noorullah got this eagle as a helpless chick from someone who had robbed a nest. The man thought he had caught a falcon, but it was not. Noorullah took this chick from that man and raised at his house in Northwest Balochistan, and the chick grew up to be a handsome male golden eagle. With this eagle, Noorullah caught several foxes, countless hares, a dozen odd jackals, a few gazelles, and once, even a half grown urial ewe!!\n\nThis photograph is dedicated to Noorullah, Laaloo, Haider and Ustad Saadullah - men who were masters of their art, but who are unfortunately no longer with us today.\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/image.php?v=Pqtxt5J][img]http://img5.imageshack.us/img5/4855/56876520.th.jpg[/img][/url]', ''),
