(30082, ' [quote=m1carbine]i have searched every  local hardware in rwp/isb.People (shopkeepers) dont know about it.Tried Stationary shops & medical stores also,but still no success. A very common thing but very hard to find it.I know its importance.[/quote]\n\nBro, its easily available in abundance in Lahore''s Urdu Bazaar. Read its specs on the net and ask the shop keeper to show you some wide tapes. you will easily spot it.\n\n[b]Its less plastic and more fabric stuff. The one doctors put to keep the bandage intact. [/b]', ''),
(30083, ' @shabbar ali\nBoth the licenses are equally well. It depends on your requirement. I would prefer a MOI license as the movement is not restricted to a single province. But at the same time I have 2 licenses issued by Sindh government and I had them All Pakistan.... this way I can use them throughout pakistan like MOI ... but one catch is that the Local Provincial government can cancel their Provincial license anytime ... whereas the MOI license cannot be cancelled by the provincial government unless a person enters into some legal issues .. then only a court can order cancellation of license.', ''),
