(30412, ' AOA Dear brothers!\ni m new to this site.i just want to have some guidence from ur vast experiences plz.\ndear friends,i just want to ask what is the difference between a 92fs clone and original? as one of my friend is having a clone ,it is gram to gram same in weight of original beretta...its finishing is  very very very fine...writing on it is exactly same as beretta and he had fired about 300 rounds in 4 months not even a single jam/missfire or chock etc...and he is using POF ammo...so question remains what is the difference b/w original and fake???\ndear members plz throw some light here too\nthx\nregards.', ''),
(30413, ' [quote=m1carbine]ka_khan sb,Hamid sb\nregarding duct tape, the yellow tape which you are asking is called mask tape,yes its ususally used to seal the boxes,The tape which is available in urdu bazar lahore that is called binding tape.Duct tape is only availble in silver color & still its availability is hard to find.Hope you will get my point.??[/quote]\n\n\nthe yellow tape being referred is called packaging tape, it is quiet strong and yellow in color used mainly by packaging and freight forwarders (execuse my spelling, just woke up, head kinda dizzy).\n\nmasking tape is ordinary tape used by car painters to mask off the area which they do not want to paint (hence the name masking tape) it is white in color and made of thin paper. available at stationary stores. very weak and low sticking power.\n\nduct tape also called shuttering tape can be of multiple colors, one side is super sticky with cotton mesh (for super strength) and other side is slippery/silver in color/shiny/plasticy type. duct tape is used to seal ventilation ducts/airconditioning ducts (hence the name, duct tape). it is super sticky, super strong and can be easily torn into various desired shapes. it is made of two layers (top layer and bottom layer made of cotton mesh soaked in sticky stuff).\n\n\nthere is a saying: if duct tape cant fix it, nothing can.\n\nthere must be a good reason why astronauts are issued duct tapes on space missions.\n\nRegards.', ''),
