(30422, ' Just thought should post a picture for my brothers as it will help in identifying different types of pressure sensitive adhesive tapes.\n\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/image.php?v=gxgjNKA][img]http://img3.imageshack.us/img3/2385/98169660.th.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[b]from left to right:\n[/b]\n1. pvc electric tape, also called electrician''s tape\n\n2. high heat electric tape, also called heat proof electric tape, thick rubbery stuff, after application turns into plastic\n\n3. masking tape, also called paper masking tape, also called auto-painter''s masking tape, made out of thin paper, low strength and less sticking power.\n\n4. scotch tape, also called transparent tape, used for sealing envelopes and stuff, good strength and good stickiness\n\n5. packaging tape, also called parcel tape, high strength and high stickiness\n\n6. duct tape, one side vinyl (silver is more common but available in other colors too) other side cotton mesh coated with super strong sticky solution, result = super strong tape, super sticky\n\n7. FSK facing tape, strong as duct tape, used for facing of the ventilation ducts but more shiny and can be cut into fine pieces.\n[b]\nRegards.[/b]\n\n[i]p.s. kindly accept my apologies for the poor quality picture, i took it from my cell phone.[/i]', ''),
