(30432, ' [quote=Omkhan]Hi all, \nI am just wondering is it safe to leave a gun with chamber loaded in car for longer period of time? \nIn summer,  a car under direct sunlight becomes an oven. I have seen ballpoint pens badly deformed & become part of the dashboard under these temperatures. What are the chances of a round go bang under these circumstances?[/quote]\n\n\nOmkhan bhai, first and foremost rule of firearm safety, never ever chamber a round unnecessarily, second, never ever leave a chambered gun unattended. third, safety on even if the gun is empty, even if u''r dead sure that its empty.\n\nif u''r a firearms owner, by law its safe handling and storage is u''r primary responsibility, even in armed forces it is adivsed to never carry chambered guns during patrolling operations. only when threat is imminent, guns are allowed to be chambered (Officer in command gives the go ahead signal, in hollywood they say lock and load, originally used fo M1Grand only)\n\nsolution: gun chamber empty, magazine full, just cock it when required.', ''),
