(30454, ' @12Gauge: Sir, no offence, but when, GOD FORBID, you fall into a situation requiring you to use your weapon, wouldn''t it be better to have a loaded, ready gun? All of us know of the crime situation in Pakistan, and its only a matter of time when one-on-one confrontations depend on who shoots first. Unlike the armed forces, we have no indication of threats in our surroundings. Waiting until the threat has revealed itself to rack the slide seems to be a tad too slow. In many situations, it''s pretty much impossible to use both hands to load the gun (I do know of single handed loading, but its a trick I would never trust). We carry guns for a simple reason: personal defence. An unloaded gun is of as much use as no gun. Today''s double action pistols are designed to be carried loaded. True, there are pistols like the TT which can go off, chambered and hammer down, but then there are others like Sig, Beretta and Stoeger, which are extremely safe.\n\nMy opinion: If you are close enough to draw a gun, it should have a full magazine, with one round down the pipe, safety PREFERABLY on. Flicking off the safety takes a fraction of a time taken racking the slide, and is a simple one-handed task.\n\n@Omkhan: Today''s polymer pistols are built to high standards and have gone through several torture tests. I, for one, do not believe that the frame can get deformed by heat accumulated in the car.\n\nOnce again, no offence intended.', ''),
