(30471, ' Dear KageFox\n\nunless u live in a cowboy/western setting where every person out there want to DRAW with ya. i would recommend, chamber empty, safety on. in real life situation, u''r weapon will be of no good to u, why? simple, enemy always strikes when he is ready and u r not.\n\never wonder why VIP security detail travels with loaded weapons and fingers off the trigger? cause they intentionally remain ready for any mishap. you on the other hand cannot remain ready all the time (u need full time staff for that). and since u cannot demonstrate that level of readiness any measure u take will be too late for any good. that is why it is recommended that chamber empty, safety on.\n\nRegards.\n\np.s. a SSG friend of mine once told me that only weapon that will help you will be the one u''ll be having at u''r home, cause thats u''r turf. if u''r mobile, u''r weapon is restricted only to boosting u''r confidence. never ever rely on it. u''r enemy never waits for u to take u''r weapon out of the dash board, under the seat, under the hand brake. similarly u''r enemy never waits for u to take u''r weapon out of u''r holster(conceal carry). kindly execuse my language but i think this is necessary.\n\na weapon is like a condom, its better to have it and not need it instead of to need it and not have it.', ''),
(30472, ' I hope you won''t mind asking a silly question: If I have a double barrel shotgun with 30 inch barrel (both barrels with fixed chokes). Now if I saw-off 6-8 inches from the barrel. Would it make it Full  Cylinder (which I want to achieve). I heard that chokes are quite near to muzzle side of barrel. I suppose that a "Short Full Cylinder Barrel Shotgun" is better for Home Defence. Please correct and guide me if I am wrong.', ''),
(30475, ' [quote=Doktar]I hope you won''t mind asking a silly question: If I have a double barrel shotgun with 30 inch barrel (both barrels with fixed chokes). Now if I saw-off 6-8 inches from the barrel. Would it make it Full  Cylinder (which I want to achieve). I heard that chokes are quite near to muzzle side of barrel. I suppose that a "Short Full Cylinder Barrel Shotgun" is better for Home Defence. Please correct and guide me if I am wrong.[/quote]\n\n\nyes, usually cylinder bores are choked near the muzzle, not exactly at the muzzle, but near to it. and if u intend to saw off 6-8 inches, u''ll probably end up with a cylinder bore.\n\nlength of the chokes usually depends on the bore the cylinder bore and if my memory serves me right, it goes something like this:\n\nlength = 1.5 to 3 times the diameter of the cylinder bore. cant remember it right, i''m sorry.\n\nmeaning if u''r cylinder bore dia is 0.729inch then length of the choke (remember choking is done in slow tappering) would be 1.0935 to 2.187 inch.\n\nregards', ''),
