(30478, ' Point taken, though I still fail to fully agree. You see, thugs these days are extremely trigger-happy. Your chances of being killed whether you comply or not remains an extreme variable. Simply put, a loaded weapon will give you a BETTER CHANCE, safety matters aside. If you offer me a 0% chance and a 1% chance on my life, which do you think will I take?\n\nIf a weapon is of no use in such a situation, than why do so many carry arms? I realize that we can never be in a state of combat readiness 24/7, but using every advantage we can avail, be it fair or unfair, is the key to staying alive.\n\nHaving a weapon is great. Not needing to use it is even greater. However, what will happen if we do NEED to USE it? After all, we left home hoping that by carrying the weapon, we might no need it...\n\nUnchambered I can understand, but unchambered, safety on? Might as well leave the weapon at home.\n\nIn the end, I apologize for any unintentional disrespect. I value your advice, but will respectfully beg to differ on this case.', ''),
