(30500, ' Get a handgun that can be carried locked n cocked (my personal preference). Draw smooth while switching off the safety in one smooth motion. Key is practice. \n\nCarrying lead in the pipe is a personal preference. While I dont agree with those who advocate racking the slide in the heat of the moment.. with enough practice it can be done in roughly the same time and has a greater deterring factor.. so they do have some valid points. You need to be real good at weapon handling (read = RESPONSIBLE) if you want to carry a round in the chamber.\n\nSecondly and coming back to the topic.. A round "cook off" happens at 200+ degrees celsius. And even then its a remote chance, especially with quality SD ammo that i''m sure all you fine folks carry. No way in hell a car''s ambient temperature will ever get THAT high. (water Boils at 100 celsius) \n\nSo relax, and rest assured the round wont go off.\n\nI would suggest and agree with the gentlemen who advise keeping a weapon away from direct sunlight and in a place not visible from outside the car when you leave it unattended. But you can keep it anywhere once you get back in the ride.\n\nApparently, the best position i''m told for in car weapon drawing is a belt cross draw, so you should holster your weapon on the  weak hand side and pull a cross draw. Also helps to keep the piece on your body than on the floor or car in case you have to disembark in a hurry and make a run for it. If you ride with a driver and/or guard in front and you as a Sahib in the backseat i think strong hand side draw would be better. But all these are preferences.. do what you think suits you.', ''),
