(30596, ' [quote=Cap1]Please guide: What''s the difference between single trigger and double trigger in O/Us? Which is better for skeet/trap?\n\nAlso, is Baikal MP-233 a good choice for skeet/trap? Availabilty and price in Karachi please?\n[url]http://www.baikalinc.ru/en/company/100.html[/url][/quote]\n\n\nA single trigger is the type that fires both barrels in a sequential order, first click bottom barrel, second click top barrel (this order can be reversed, also sometimes, by default it could be top barrel first then bottom barrel second). anyways point is the barrels fire in a sequential manner.\n\nA double trigger is the type where one trigger fires the bottom barrel and second trigger fires the top barrel. since there is a seperate trigger for each barrel, there is no need for a trigger selector (a button or a device that determines which barrel will fire first, found only on single trigger o/u)\n\npreference: hmm.... difficult to answer, kindly allow me to break it down for ya\n\n[b]double trigger:[/b]\n\n[b]pros:[/b]\n\n1. blazing fast trigger\n2. highly reliable trigger mechanism\n3. instant (on the go type) barrel selection, fire the desired barrel instantly\n4. less prune to doubling\n5. no such thing as wrong trigger selection, only that barrel will fire whose trigger is squeezed\n\n[b]cons:[/b]\n\n1. requires considerable training to develop necessary skill in selecting right trigger for the job\n2. alot confusing in the heat of the moment\n3. difficult to manuever/use (my opinion only) with gloves\n4. trigger feel is different for both triggers (my opinion only). however in high end o/u this might not be a problem.\n\n[b]single trigger:[/b]\n\n[b]pros:[/b]\n\n1. extremely simple to use, single trigger for both barrels, u cant miss it\n2. for those who are used to pumps and semiautos, its a blessing\n3. for a simple bloke such as myself, it makes the job alot easier\n\n[b]cons:[/b]\n\n1. decreased life compared to double trigger\n2. prune to doubling\n3. trigger can develop excessive creep after considerable use\n4. barrel selection is extremely difficult "on the go", in the heat of the moment, barrel slection is extremely difficult if not impossible.\n5. sometimes u forget which barrel will fire first, its not the trigger fault, its basically operator fault associated with this type of trigger\n\n[b]to summarize:[/b]\n\nits like comparing an automatic (single trigger) camera to a manual (double trigger) camera. automatic will automatically correct the colors, focus, contrast etc. it will make u''r job alot easier as there are less variables to consider but then again, automatic will do only so many things, a manual camera on the other hand is difficult to use, it will be confusing, u''ll probably endup ruining u''r shots, but some of the most beautiful shots are actually taken by manual cameras, u simply cannot beat the things a manual camera can do in the hands of an expert camera man. there must be a reason why almost all professional camera-men u hear or read about use manual cameras (digital or regular).\n\n[b]Regards.[/b]\n\n[i]p.s. i prefer single trigger, double trigger always confuse the hell out of me. and yes!, i also prefer automatic cameras over manual cameras. :D in the end it all falls down to personal preference[/i]', ''),
