(30637, ' google around buddy, u''ll find plenty of well written articles on the subject. and one more thing, standard practice is to stand at a distance of 40yards from the target. target size is irrelevent, however it should be large enough to accomodate a 30inch circle (complete pattern) with a 15inch inner circle (it represents the dense part of the pattern).\n\nat 40 yards, or 37meters, 70% of pellets should fall in the 30inch or 76cm circle with full choke, 60% with modified, 50% with improved cylinder.\n\nhope it helps.\n\nRegards.\n\nfor skeet, standard practice is to stand at 20 yards from the target. i would highly recommend that u google a bit, plenty of well written and highly explained articles are available on the subject. the articles will also explain if u''r shooting high or low.', ''),
