(30752, ' [quote=MUSTANIR]BUT u will c dat Russian hits higher dan normal semis.... I sold min coz I missd those wingy rascals too... either u adjust or get rid.[/quote]\n\n\nhold u''r horses bro, russian guns dont hit higher than normal. allow me to explain.\n\nrussian guns are made with typical european standards of short length of pull (distance between trigger and where the buttstock ends). to put it in simple words, russian use shorter buttstocks.\n\nhaving said that, if a gun''s length of pull is short for a shooter it will cause it to shoot high, if a gun''s length of pull is long for a shooter, it will cause the shooter to shoot low.\n\na shotguns fit is very important, lemme repeat very important, unfortunately most people dont even know how to get their shotgun fitted to their body, once fitted, brother! u''ll be amazed, a properly fitted gun doesnt even need open eyes to mount and aim, once u get u''r shotgun fitted, just close u''r eyes mount and aim, open u''r eyes and u''ll be dead smack on the target.\n\nthis is exactly the reason i requested the starter of this post to google around and read a few articles, LOP (length of pull) is just one variable to consider, there are many such as cast, comb, drop and each and every one of the variables change the point of impact of the pellets.\n\nRegards.\n\np.s. i didnt even hire the services of a gun fitter, i did it myself, had to add two inches to the LOP of my guns, man! what  a difference it makes, makes shooting absolutely reflexive in nature. aiming needs are totally diminished, just mount the gun, look at the target and u''r gun will automatically follow.', ''),
(30755, ' [quote=TAREEN]The precision tools used by some of our gunsmiths are awesome. Hands & eyes... Although they might not be appreciated by some. ;)\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/image.php?v=Pq1RdgIi][img]http://img190.imageshack.us/img190/7681/70889798.th.jpg[/img][/url][/quote]\n\nDear All\n\nThis is really awesome, our people are very talented, confident and perfect. I salute them.\nRegards to all.', ''),
(30756, ' thought should post this picture, it''ll help u guyz alot. i''m also thinking about writing a proper article on do-it-youself shotgun fit but it''ll have to wait till sunday.\n\n[img]http://www.skbshotguns.com/images/old%20website/85tss_stock.jpg[/img]\n\nLOP = length of pull\nDAH = drop at heel\nDAC = drop at comb\nLOTP = length of trigger pull\n\nlook at the lower right side of this image, u''ll see "cast" of a shotgun\n\n[img]http://perazzi.com/Contents/Images/Catalogo/Tabella_calci.jpg[/img]\n\n\nand one more thing, kindly read this article, it explicitly says russian make shotguns with shorter length of pull and if u adjust it to u''r body it shoots dead center.\n\n[url]http://www.shootingtimes.co.uk/guns/197256/Baikal_12bore_shotgun_test.html[/url]\n\nRegards.', ''),
