(30822, ' My advice would be not to sell it. It is a historical piece, and unless one is extremely hard-pressed for money, the Walther P-38 is something to keep.\n\nIts value is less due to its inherent usefulness (compared to today''s Wondernines), and a lot more due to the fact that is was issued to German officers in World War II, alongside the Luger P-08 pistol. According to Wiki, "the P-38 was the first locked-breech pistol to use a double-action trigger".\n\nAnyway, if you still want to go on, best of luck on your sale.', ''),
