(30940, ' I think we are talking about the same thing and arguing as wel. What ever is tiliting towards the shooter for me is tiliting away from the shooter for you. But if i say CAST OFF for the right handed shooter and CAST ON for the left handed shooter it is acceptable for you and for me, and exactly that is what we are saying.\n\nThanks for providing the formula to determine the length of pull for a person. As far as your generous offer of helping me in finding the gun fit is considered i really appreciate it as i never owned a shotgun and seldom shot one........ :D even then i feel no harm in finding a perfect measure. This will add to my cyber knowldge of shotguns, handguns and rifles.\n\nI feel great that i was able to approximate your hight by just reading about your gun customization. I must have droped the argument have you added boxing along with your basketball experience. :)\n\nI am 5'' 10" so have never considered about LOP as all manufecturing is being done for this hight. According to your formula LOP of your gun should be as follows\n(6*(3.175)+361.95)=381mm\nLet us convert this into inches:\n381*(.03937)=15"\n\nVery interesting i really enjoyed the calculations.', ''),
