(30943, ' [quote]I am 5'' 10" so have never considered about LOP as all manufecturing is being done for this hight. According to your formula LOP of your gun should be as follows\n(6*(3.175)+361.95)=381mm\nLet us convert this into inches:\n381*(.03937)=15"[/quote]\n\nbrother I said: add 3.175mm for every inch taller u r from a 5''9 male. since u''r 5''10, that is, one inch taller to a 5''9 man, then the mathematical approximation in u''r case would be:\n\nformula 1 LOP = 1*(3.175) + 361.95 = 365.175 = 14.375 inch (for winter hunting)\n\nformula 2 LOP = 1*(3.175) + 368.3 = 371.475 = 14.625 inch (for hot summer hunting/summer skeet)\n\nI use formula 2, in my case it is easier for me to adjust to a slightly longer LOP then to a shorter, otherwise general rule is to opt for formula 1. plus I dont hunt that often. \n\nbut then again, this mathematical approximation doesn''t take individual sleeve length into consideration, infact it takes average values for the sleeve length (average sleeve length of 5''9 north american male).\n\nRegards.', ''),
