(30956, ' @12 gauge, i am very much aware of the fit of the shotgun. It is as important for shotgun as important for the rifle are its sights. As in shotgun shooting there is no need of the front beed if gun fits to the shooter and shooter mounts the gun correctly. As we all know shotguns are shot both eyes opened and dominant eye of the shooter just behind the sight plane focused on the target. These all things point towards just one thing and that is fit of the shotgun. If the gun will not fit to the shooter there will be a below average shooting.\n\nAt the same time i am also aware of the fact that gun fit is not an absolute science of perfections but just a  \nbetter approximations of art. As killing range of shotguns dosen''t involve great distances and at the same time neither a pointblank perfeection(keeping in view the size of the pattern). So we can buy a readymade suit of an approximate size or get a tailor made for exact measurements. They both will serve the pupose unless we have bought a wrong size of a readymade garment. \n\nI am a practical rifle guy but a shotgun lover as wel, as they are my first love. So importance of sights to me is a much serious consideration as compared to a shotgun felow.', ''),
