(31067, ' I belong to a middle class family as well. I Suggest that we should alteast do the following to be safe; \n\n1. At first we need to educate our family members and friends about the responses that one should be have during crisis\n2. We need to identify the possible areas where one can be threatened\n3. If you have a wapon then educate all adults about the safety precausions and how to use it in case of emergency (for Self Defence ONLY)\n4. As far as security of your valuables are concerned, the only advice would be, not to keep all your eggs in one basket (always scatter your valuble in seperate places)\n5. Please visit CPLC web-site for security instructions, they are really good. \n6. Never try to complete the scene by your self only... always seek help (call 15 or call your friends or family member to call 15 on behalf of you) \n7. Always make sure that your network of friends or relatives is there when you need them\n8. In case of any such miss-hap of break-in, bring all your family members in a room which is safe (strong doors, ideally have a cell-phone, some supplies (like water or food or First-aid stuff), Gun is good to have )\n9. In case if you are sure that the treat is reall and there is no false alarm then you can call police and fire some arial shots as a deterent. Gun fights are only good for movies (Always play safe, specially when your family is around)\n10. End of it one should be respectful to humanity and should always be bid with country laws (hence study them, they tells you about your rights)', ''),
