(31495, ' For the Stoeger, you MIGHT be able to get a laser which could clamp onto the front of the trigger guard. Don''t know any provisions for light though.\n\nHaving a flashlight with the gun in a self defence situation is really useful, but then, everywhere a beam from a mounted light goes, the muzzle of a loaded, ready-to-go gun goes. I am not sure that I want the muzzle to be pointed in places it shouldn''t be. \n\nAs far as laser dots are concerned, my preference would be something integrated into the grips, like Crimson Trace, though I understand that it is a more expensive option. In my humble opinion, laser dots are more useful in the hands of a trained Special Forces member, rather than a civilian. I am willing to concede to the fact that laser dots do make aiming in the dark easier, but it takes a lot of practice.\n\nNow if they could make lights/lasers much more obtrusive (as in not requiring different holsters) the whole rail problem would cease to exist.', ''),
