(31550, ' Any specific reason for the two restricted choices?\n\nGiven the choice, I wouldn''t go for either gun. The Walther P22 (.22Lr) is a good, well made reliable pistol, but the fact remains that the .22 caliber is not much of a self defence round. That, and the fact the misfires are common in .22LR ammo, due to its nature (rimfire as compared to centrefire as in 9mm).\n\nThe .22LR round is not a very viable option as a personal defence round. In contrast, the 9mm is a much better option. Though, a .22 pistol is the best self-defence option for the handicapped or the elderly.\n\nI don''t know why but I wouldn''t want to trust my life to local made guns. I know that there are some very good pieces out there but... reliability is still a factor.\n\nIF given the above two to choose from, I would go with the Walther P22, due to it being compact and easy to carry. Cheap ammo will allow me to find the brand the gun likes best.', ''),
