(31955, ' AOA Guys, \n\nWell check out the below link which might help you in making your decision about CF98. \n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=15qsJgnm0sw[/url]\n\nAs far as NP-42 is concerned it would be very difficult to find nowadays as CF98 is more in the market due to the transfer of manufacturing to Chang Feng Machinery Tools from where it gets its designation as CF. By the way Chang Feng is working under NORINCO. \n\nAs for my experience, i fired 50 rounds in about 20 mins from my CF98, without any jam or misfire, fired at a range of more then 50 meters, having pretty accurate results. Recoil is minimum as you can see in the video, but if you loosen your grip then it will definitely give a big recoil, which you guys can also see in the video as i did loosen my grip a few times.\n\nIts a robust weapon which can fire any type of bullet be it chinese, russian 9mm luger, POF or american. It can fire even DAP rounds. \n\nGuys do keep in mind that CF98 or NP42 has become the standard weapon of the Chinese Army, Police, Hong Kong Police and also as Type-92 of Bangladesh Army, which would mean that this is a pretty good & reliable weapon good as Chinese don''t induct average weapons. The chinese TT is a good example in front of you, which has been in service for decades now and is like by nearly everyone as its a strong and reliable weapon. And today''s CF98 are 8000 round barrel life which is more then enough for ppl who wish to keep it as a SD weapon. \n\nCF98 in Peshawar is for 35K nowadays. The one i bought has CF98-9mm written on it with a Shaheen Logo. \n\nI had pasted the image on some of the CF98 related forums. \n\nWould like to have your guys feed back also. \n\nThx', ''),
