(32109, ' [quote]Thanks guys ! I bought it for 50k and the price for both the wooden and fiber ones is the same. It comes with 4 chokes, one installed and three extra. The year of manufacture is 2007. It is 4+1.[/quote]\n\nexcellent purchase, 2007 is a good model. enjoy ur new purchase.\n\n[quote]@12Guage. Thanks will do. In a nutshell is there anything specific break in that you recommend ?[/quote]\n\nbreak-in proceedure is pretty simple, just fire 100-200 typical hunting cartridges cartridges before trying out lighter loads.\n\nanother new discovery in the break-in I read somewhere is that just load two snap caps or fired/spent cartridges in the magazine tube and then simply pull the cocking handle then dry fire then cycle the cocking handle/bolt manually as this will eject the snap cap/cartridge and load the other one into the chamber then dry fire again and maually cycle the cocking handle/bolt. do this proceedure 100 times and you are finished with the break-in proceedure.\n\ntry this, theoratically, i dont see a reason why this proceedure shouldnt work. as far as plain theory or mechanics is concerned, break-in is just supposed to cycle to the gun multiple time in order to settle all working parts in their desired position and rub/grind the action smooth to permit easy future cycling.\n\nRegards.', ''),
