(161943, ' Thank you Mr. Ahmed Sultan, Mr. Denovo and all my friends. We definitely owe it to the abundance of good wishes that Meshall has performed well in her first international event. I am sorry no medals the first time.  Mr. SF I think CCTV (China) is doing partial live coverage and is available through internet.  \nA little anecdote, Mr. Bata once sent two executives to Africa to access market potential for his shoes. One of them returned and reported that it is zero as all go barefoot. The other assessed that a huge potential exists as so many people need shoes.\nSo, here are a few results of our shooters alongwith the top scores. The task of coming up to their levels could either be taken as absolutely hopeless OR lets take a shot.\n\n50m free pistol     - Gold=565/600     Kaleem=539 (30th)           Kaleem Khan=531 (37th)     Total=43\n10m air pistol       - Gold=585/600     Kaleem Khan=563 (36th)   Kaleem=562 (37th)             Total=50\n10m air pistol       - Gold=383/400     Meshall=375 (24th)            Tazeem=366 (41st)             Total=52\n10m air rifle         - Gold=399/400     Urooj=390 (34th)                Nazish=384 (47th)              Total=54\n50m rifle prone    - Gold=595/600     Urooj=565 (47th)                Nazish=561 (50th)              Total=50\n\nSome catching up to do!', ''),
