(381513, ' @Mig\nI''m sorry for my language bro, I meant no offense to anyone. If I caused any anybody any stress then I most sincerely apologize. Thanks for pointing it out. :-)\n\nYou''re right bro, the Law is simply out-dated and antiquated. It''s in dire need of an overhaul, along with a rethinking of our current gun laws and attitudes towards firearms in general. I think it''s high time we legally begin to accept a couple of things:-\n\n1)  Weapons are MUCH easier to procure than licenses\n2)  ANYBODY can get their hands on automatic weapons\n3)  Firearm forensics & techniques simply don''t exist in Pakistan\n4)  Although we, as a nation, feel that it is our God-given right to bear arms, we are not willing to accept the great responsibility that comes with it\n\nI think ultimately even if we modernize the laws, it will make little or no difference because we, as a people, are simply unwilling to change. For example, despite knowing the hazards and potentially fatal outcomes of aerial firing, every Tom, Dick & Harry continues to blast away! It''s so unfortunate that we''re simply unwilling to take the gravity and seriousness of our actions.\n\nInfact, a lot of people simply consider their guns to be toys for grownups!', ''),
