(32479, ' The top one is an original Israeli Uzi 9mm semi auto pistol. Honestly it looks ugly and as it is semi auto I really can''t think of any use with such sahpe, which is more suitable to full auto lead sprayers.\n\nThe second one is US made Cobray M11/M12 series. These pistols were discontinued long time back, the company which manufactured these closed down many years ago. There is however some stock still available in NIB condition which was manufactured about 15 years back.\n\nNo spare parts are available even in the USA. The guns are not accurate and very hard to control in full auto mode and are generally refered to as spray and pray, as the shooter is never sure of hitting his targets, ammo is too expensive to waste like that.\n\nMy advice, don''t fall for the cool looks, keep away from these guns.', ''),
