(32542, ' First of all i feel sorry for the controversy about the availability of RUGERS with BUKSH ELAHI as i was mistakenly under the impression that the said dealer still has these guns. Although i will try to persuade another dealer who is quite helpful to me, to import these fine guns as soon as possible(i am also interested in purchasing the said gun). I have got imported few weapons before.\n\nNow about the test firing of ABBAS''s gun. I also enjoyed firing the RUGER, pistol has a bull barrel, crisp trigger, excellent balance, comfortable grip, easily accessible controls and nice adjustable(rear, also drilled for scope) sights. Gun fired flawlessly during the entire shooting session that wasn''t short. We used three types of bullets, hollow points, ELEY sporter. RWS 22 CLUB, all went flawlessly. I think the gun is made to break the myth about being ammo selective of the 22 semi auto pistols. The gun is ideal for target shooting and small game hunting as it has 6 and half inches long bull barrel with excellent accuracy. Gun is also ideal for learning shooting as it has full size dimensions of big bores and economy of 22lr. In short the gun is an excellent purchase and is a must have for every shooter.', ''),
