(32634, ' Quail is a collective name for several genera of mid-sized birds in the pheasant family Phasianidae. New World quails (family Odontophoridae) and buttonquails (family Turnicidae) are not closely related but named for their similar appearance and behaviour.\n\n\nIn his posthumously published Meditations, the Roman Emperor Marcus Aurelius mentions quail-fighting, so we know that the practice is at least two thousand years old and probably far older. \nQuail fighting is a common hobby in Pushtun society. Once a Batair (fighting quail) runs away from the Maidaan (quail fighting arena) then it loses its heart and cannot face even a weaker quail to fight, hence is called “Bhagail Marraz”. Usually such quails are slaughtered by the Batair Baaz (quail betters) for a delicious roast.\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img12.imageshack.us/img12/2683/69534939.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nSerious injuries are far more common among hockey players, and birds have no teeth to get knocked out. \n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img12.imageshack.us/img12/3034/57300720.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img12.imageshack.us/img12/5185/59220638.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img12.imageshack.us/img12/9127/38158861.jpg[/img][/url]\nWatching the actual fight often consists of seeing the two birds strut about for a minute then go into a spinning ball of feathers. Suddenly one of the birds shoots out of the feather ball and runs away.He is the Looser !\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sh1rtqhj_aQ[/url]', ''),
