(32728, ' There is no such difference. Basically 636 is the batch number of production. The 636 model is the latest one which has a computerized number written on the gun. The older models had numbers punched on the gun. Well this is basically a difference between an older and newer model which makes the older punched model to be more of value. This is what ive heard from dealers. There is not only 636 model but also 766 and 99 model. These numbers indicate the batch number of production. I have also heard that the older punched models were originally made by norinco whereas the present models 636 or 766 or even the other chinese handguns are being made by subsidiary or sister companies of norinco hence being of lesser value. In the market both 636 and older punched model is also available. If you get 636 for 20k new then the punched one will cost you 30k for the new one.', ''),
