(32833, ' There is NO need to continually disassemble the parts down to the nitty gritty bhai.  Here is what I have been doing for the past five years with my Ruger.  For one thing these pistols that you and I have are in Stainless... no need no let me rephrase IT WILL NOT RUST.  Just pop the action back - remove the grips - spray 3M Brake Cleaner or Brichwood Casey Gun Scrubber - then lubricate.  Thats it.  I know its new and all and you want to go through everything but you will find that these two items CLEAN the gun thoroghly.  And you have to come here it will be fun shooting.\nAlso I have found a Ruger MK II Bull Barrel stainless new in box (the one you have is called a slabside) the dealer wants tooo much money for it... about two lacs, I think it wise to still buy it at 140lacs considering one of the things many don''t know is that Ruger does NOT sell to Pakistan - they used to but NOT anymore, its their company policy and not the law.\nNow that the bug has bitten you... what about customizing it like mine with some goodies.  Volquartsen Custom is the BEST along with Clarks Custom.  Visit them at [url]https://www.volquartsen.com/.[/url]  I have their custom trigger set, sight, slide release, and mag release.  \nKeep Plinking (shooting).', ''),
