(33035, ' [quote=CAP]Cool gun Faisal, congrats. And at US prices too :). Do explain in the appropriate section how 4th Gen differs from 3rd Gen.[/quote]\n\n\nThanks a lot, I really appreciate all of you for the compliments. 4th Gen has a different texture of grip, its kind of material which sticks to your hand much better than previous model also finger groves are slightly smaller in size making it more comfortable and grip-able to hold. Another difference I have noticed after shooting it side by side with my other Glocks is that this model has a lighter trigger pull. \nOver all, most of the people here, including myself are of the opinion that previous version looked more prettier than 4th Gen, however it is more convenient to hold. Even after its release, still majority of people prefer to buy Glock 21SF with Picatinny rail.', ''),
