(33078, ' @Tarzen, there are other dealers who charge you a lot less..17k is a lot some dealers are even offering MOI licenses within a month for 15k. Last i heard provincial licenses to be made for 12-14k. Well i could be of some help if you tell me which zone do you live in like east or other. If you live in the east side and your TPO/DIG lies in Gulshan side then i can refer you to a dealer who can make all sindh license for 12-14k within 20 days. They are actually having problems for police verifications in other zones.\n@Memon, the direct process is too hectic and nearly impossible to go on with. If nothing happens you will be waiting for your book for months and in the end you will have to pay a hefty amount to get your book. The direct process however sounds simple but is not. You first have to download the form from sindh home dept website and then fill it in. You will have to take the filled form and the verification form to the dco and then he will keep the form and tell you to get the verification form filled by your TPO and DIG. After youve done that and submitted it to the dco, you simply relax for an indefinite time period and then your form will be fwded to the home dept. After approval from home dept. they will ask you to bring the challan paid from the post office. After submitting the challan you will again have to relax and wait for an indefinite period and then you will start visiting the dco asking them for your book but in the end they will either ask you upfront money and you will pay them or you will loose hope and forget about the license. And one day you will get a call to collect your license finally lol :D hows that..\nEarlier on when the powers rested with the Dco''s it was a little easier and would cost you less but now without prior approval from the home dept. no license can be issued by the Dco.', ''),
(33079, ' 12Gauge... No Bro, a piece means a single bullet :) If you call 120 for a serbian JHP being expensive, plz don''t ask how\nmuch many handgun lovers pay for a single Hydrashock bullet :lol: \n@someone who has bought it recently... plz amaze our beloved brother 12Gauge, a bit more by quoting the price :)\nFew days back, a dealer in Peshawar (who''s known to be expensive) quoted 400 a piece to me... don''t worry I didn''t\nbuy any, coz I was only willing to spend upto 250 per piece :D', ''),
