(33319, ' Besides knowledge, skill, good equipment and luck ... hunting also demands determination, persistence and hard work.  Today I would like to introduce one of my hunters Mr. Gregory Bond, from USA. He is around 60 year old. Physically, over weight & suffers from pain in joints (especially his knees are very painful). So it''s always a challenge for him to walk uphill. In Feb 2009, Mr. Bond shot a Sindh Ibex & Blandford Urial for which he had to walk all the way to the top of two hilly habitats and undertook 8 hours of walk for each of his hunts. During these long & hard walks, he felt so breathless and suffered so much pain in his knees any other macho man would have given up. But I salute Mr. Bond that under these odd physical conditions and quite a hot weather he accomplished his hunts. At home, the Dallas Safari Club awarded him the best hunter of the year. I''m pleased to show a couple of photos of Mr. Bond with his recent hunts in Pakistan as follows.\n\n[img]http://pakistanguides.com/hunting/hunt_pix/greg_bond_blandford_urial_hr3.JPG[/img]\n\n[img]http://pakistanguides.com/hunting/hunt_pix/greg_bond_sindh_ibex_hr3.JPG[/img]', ''),
