(33345, ' "The Pakistan Arms Ordinance\n(XX OF 1965)\n[8th June, 1965}\nAn Ordinance to consolidate and amend the law relating to the sale, transport; bearing or\npossession of arms, ammunition or military stores.....\n\n(b) "arms" includes—\n(i) cannon;\n(ii) fire-arms of all types, such as light and heavy automatic and semiautomatic weapons, rifles,\ncarbines, muskets, shotguns (whether single or double barreled), revolvers, pistols and [b]appliances\nthe object of which is the silencing of fire-arms;[/b]\n(iii) air pistols, bayonets, swords, sword-sticks daggers, knives with blades of four inches or more\n(but not kitchen knives or knives used in good faith for the carrying on of a profession and flickknives\nirrespective of the blade ;"\n\n(iv) knuckle-dusters, spears, spear-heads, bows and arrows and parts of arms ;\n\n(c)[b] "cannon"[/b] includes—\n(i) all types of artillery, mortars, machine and sub-machine guns;\n(ii)[b] silencers for all machines and sub-machine guns[/b]\n\nAs you gentlemen see, silencer for handguns and semi auto weapons are considered ARMS\n\nSilencers for SMGs and assault rifles are considered part of cannon.\n\nNow for what is prohibited..\n\n4. Unlicensed sale and repair prohibited\n5. Power to prohibit transport\n8. Prohibition of going armed without licence\n9. Unlicensed possession of arms etc\n\nAND what happens when you go against the above...\n\n[b]13. Penalty for breach of Sections 4, 5, 8 to 11[/b]: Subject to the provisions of Sees. 13-A and 13-B,\nwho ever commits any of the following offences, namely:-—\n(a) sells, or keeps, offers or exposes for sale, any arms, ammunition or military stores, or under\ntakes the repairs of any arms in contravention of\nthe provisions of Section 4 ;\n(b) fails to give notice of the sale of arms and ammunition and of the purchaser''s name and address\nas required by Section 4 ;\n(c) transports any arms, ammunition or military stores in contravention of a regulation or\nprohibition issued under Section 5 ;\n\n\n(d) goes armed in contravention of the provisions of Section 8 ;\n(e) has in his possession or under his control any arms, ammunition or military stores in\ncontravention of the provisions of Section 9 ;\n(f) fails to deposit arms, ammunition or military stores as required by Section 10 ;\n(g) intentionally makes any false entry in a record or account which by a rule make under clause (d)\nof Section 11 he is required to keep ;\n(h) intentionally fails to exhibit anything which by a rule made under clause (f) of Section 11 he is\nrequired to exhibit ; or\n(i) [b]keeps[/b], carries or displays any arms in contravention of an order issued under Section 11-B ;\nshall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may [b]extend to seven years or with fine, or\nwith both :[/b]\n\never sells, or keeps, offers or exposes for sale a [b]cannon[/b], grenade, bomb, rocket or a light or heavy\nautomatic or semi-automatic weapon, such as klashnikov, a G-lll rifle or any other type of assault\nrifle, or ammunition which can be fired from such weapon, in contravention of the provisions of\nSection 4, shall be punishable with [b]imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years\nand shall not be less than seven years, fine and forfeiture of property.[/b]\n\n\n13-B. Penalty for breach of Section 8 or Section 9 in respect of [b]cannon[/b] or automatic weapon,\netc.: Whoever: —\n{a) [b]goes armed with a cannon[/b], grenade, bomb, rocket or a light or heavy automatic weapon, such as\na klashinkov, a G-lll rifle or any other type of\nassault rifle, in contravention of the provisions of Section 8; or\n(b} has in his possession or under his control any of the arms or weapons referred to in clause (a),\nor ammunition which can be fired from such weapon, in contravention of Section 9 ;\nshall be [b]punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years and shall not be\nless than three years and fine.[/b]\n\n\nAs you can see, it is clearly illegal to own and possess a suppressor in Pakistan unless you get a license made from the Federal Government which would not be impossible in the current government as it would be the same as a PB license.\n\n\nBesides, where do you plan to procure subsonic bullets from as the suppressor you would get after so much khwaari would be useless without subsonic ammo?\n\nSonic boom anyone?\n\nBest is to get an MP5SD3 on a PB license.. kill two birds with one stone.. \n\nIf any of you fine gentlemen have any queries regarding the understanding of the law stated above I would be more than happy to assist.\n\nRegards', ''),
