(33370, ' FYI\n\n\n-----------------------\nInterior Ministry issues new SOPs for arms licences\n\nBy Tahir Niaz\n\nISLAMABAD: The Interior Ministry on Tuesday issued a new set of standard operating procedures (SOPs) to ensure transparency, prevent malpractices and streamline the process of issuing arms licences.\n\nSources said under the new SOPs, the interior secretary would approve applications for non-prohibited bore (NPB) arms licenses, while applications for prohibited bore (PB) arms licenses would have to be approved by the interior minister, the minister of state for interior or by the prime minister.\n\nA demand notice would be issued within 10 days of the approval of the application.\n\nA copy of the national identity card, the original paid challan receipt, two photographs, police verification (by the concerned district police officer) or duly certified by any MNA, MPA or senator, would be the pre-requisites for obtaining a license.\n\nThe licence would be issued after 20 days of the completion of the above requirements, the sources said.\n\nThe fee for new arms licenses has been fixed at Rs 5,000 for NPB and Rs 7,500 for PB licence. Once prepared, the licences would be issued to the applicants in person. Copies of the arms licenses would be issued only after the approval of the interior secretary or by an officer authorised by him.\n\nMeanwhile, a meeting of the sub-committee of Standing Committee on Interior was held at Parliament House, with Interior Secretary Kamal Shah informing the committee that action was being taken against corrupt officials in the arms licensing branch.\n\nSource: [url]http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2009\\07\\08\\story_8-7-2009_pg7_26[/url]', ''),
