(33672, ' Known for the rolling grasslands studded with multicolored flowers, sporadic windstorms, haunting desolation and enthralling wildlife, Pakistan is so blessed to domain the seldom visited Deosai Plateau (now a national park & protected area). Located in the southwest-northwest of Skardu, at 4,300 meters (14,000 feet) its is the natural habitat of the Great Himalayan Brown Bear (equivalent to American Grizzly Bear). The undulating slopes of Deosai Plateau are also comprised of the shy and pretty Himalayan Marmots along with several summer swamps where mosquitoes breed, a unique replica of Arctic Tundra with many interesting alpine and Arctic plant forms. Most species bloom at the same time - during the brief summer of July and August when, addition to sedges, grasses and dwarf willows, many plants grow in tufts and some form compact cushions.\n\nThis plateau is approximately 100 sq miles in area. Since Deosai is a tree-less plateau (located above tree line) and its composed of small undulating hills with rolling grassland, and if you see a bear, it cant escape and you can see it walk away for miles & miles. \n\nThis bear is on the list of protected species of the WWF and it is taken very good care by a very organized community based program. It''s hunting is totally forbidden ... and as per the last survey I read long time ago their surving number was just 22 bears the current population is around 50 and I hope and pray it thrives by leaps & bounds ! ... so our grand children may see this cute animal ! \n\nSo my dear friends .. just imagine .. if something goes wrong ... and if all of these 22 (or so) number of bears are killed, dead with desease or God fobid wiped out from the face of the Earth due to any other reason ... we''ll never get it back & it will be an irreparable loss for Pakistan ! \n\nSO LET''S GO ALL TOGETHER AND SHOOT THESE BEARS .... but with our cameras only ! ... it''ll be a great fun !\n\n[img]http://i560.photobucket.com/albums/ss46/pakistanguides/HimalaynBrownBearDeosai.jpg[/img]\n\nLook how cute this guy looks ! I bet It''s much more beautiful than any other specie of the bear in the world. Photo made by Zahoor Ahmed !\n\n[img]http://i560.photobucket.com/albums/ss46/pakistanguides/BrownBearAtDeosaiByImran-1.jpg[/img]\n\nAnd here is another photo by M. Imran from Flikr.', ''),
