(33714, ' I totally agree that everyone has the right to do whatever they want within the confines of their homes, but thats why you have zoning laws (atleast on paper) to ensure that the rights of your neighbors are also protected. You might not have a problem with someone shooting behind your boundary wall but i definitely have an issue. Who is going to ensure that a wayward bullet will not ricochet and hurt/kill somone close by. I would not like to wait and see before something happens. Thats foolishness IMO. There is no justification for a back yard range, in a urban/residential setting. \n\nNot having a shooting range close by does not give anyone the right to use a residential home for the said purpose, besides being illegal. \n\nAs far as silencers go, i have nothing for/against them. They do have a recreation aspect. Besides whoever wants to hurt/kill someone they will find one way or the other to achieve their target. Silencers are restricted (but not illegal) in most countries, i''m sure there are good justifications behind them being so. \n\nwarm regards', ''),
