(381420, ' [QUOTE=HaroonNazir;219467]Well done????\r\nThis is not a game this is meat collecting. I pity that due to people like this the game in our country have become more of bag boosting than game. .[/QUOTE]\r\nUsually I don''t like to comment on post like yours but since you are new to this forum I will try to get the message across; My friend this is a hunting forum and we as a community, fully endorse all legal hunting. For Quail hunting in Sindh, the wildlife shooting permit allows one to shoot six days a week with an unlimited bag limit. With that in mind, we have hunted two days in the entire season and those two days were spent enjoying in good company and great quail shooting.  \r\n\r\nI appreciate and enjoy pics being posted here by different members of their hunt and in return post my hunting pics for other to see. Bag is only one aspect of a good hunt, we also post pics of the entire experience. So don''t let the bag pics upset you. \r\n\r\n[QUOTE=HaroonNazir;219467]\r\nWhy no tahe out your frustation on skeets than killing hundred and hundred of birds. Hunting is about few good shorts and to remeber those moments. Killing like this one needs a giggga bit memory to remember the shorts. \r\n[/QUOTE]\r\nFrom your comments I see that its you who is frustrated. For your information, I do skeet shooting and enjoy that also. I certainly don''t require you to tell me what hunting or skeet shooting is about. You can have your opinion but stop telling others what to do. \r\n\r\n[QUOTE=HaroonNazir;219467]I am sorry for my harsh\r\n[/QUOTE] \r\nDon''t do or say things for which you have to be sorry :-)', ''),
