(34049, ' [quote=PakistanGuides][quote=Turumti]I have heard of a 36" urial being taken by a local hunter. I didnt see the trophy, but I have little reason to doubt him, as the man has some of the best trophies you will ever see.\n\nAs for ibex, I think the largest so far has been a 52" shot a by a local hunter. \n\nFinally, regarding poaching, I consider shooting females and young ones poaching, shooting animals from helicopters is poaching. But a nice big male taken fairly is not poaching. It''s all a question of ethics.[/quote]\n\nLol ... my dear Turumti Jee before I reply you, let me first underline your comment starting with "FINALLY" !\n\nNo I''m afraid I & millions of ethical hunters & conservators around the world will not agree with your above or any other definition of poaching because it has become an established fact that any hunting that is done without procuring license from your Govts, paying the hunting permit fees or generating fiscal benefit for the conserving community or contributing to the conservation of the animals which you are hunting  and/or hunting in off season or hunting over and above the prescribed bag limits or usinf traps .. etc are all illegal forms of hunting and falls in the category of poaching ... no matter whatever logic, reasoning and justrification you give ...! It''s just like some pathans from NWFP justifying their smuggling as legitimate business ...! and when you listen to their logic and reasons ... you get so easily convinced that they are right but actually they are not ![/quote]\n\nKaiser Sahab, \n\nWho do you think the poachers in Pakistan are? The man who shoots an urial with his single barrel shotgun to get some meat deep in the heart of Balochistan, hundreds of miles from the nearest K&N outlet. Or the moneyed shikaries who drive out to the border line, courtesy of their connection with karnal falaana and brigadier dhamaka, and then rip loose on chinkaras, pharas, and nilgai with shotguns and SMGs, wound half a dozen animals, collect only one, and let the other five die a miserable death. \n\nMy friend the ultimate law is your conscience. \n\nAs for permits not being fairly issued to Pakistani hunters, let me quote a verse from Allama Iqbal here, "Jis Khet Se Dehkaan Ko Muyassar Nahi Rozi;\nUss Khet Ke Har Koshah-e-Gandum Ko Jala Do!!', ''),
(34051, ' Nice show M.HAMZA. Good to see another ethical & law abiding hunter.', ''),
(34052, ' Looks like I''m a "Black Crow" (FA Pass - BA Pending) among a flock of "White Pigeons" (So Many MBAs)\n\nBut I''m so lucky that Allah converted my hobby into my profession. I serve hunters, climbers & trekkers for just 3 months in a year & then I’m off for a long vacation of 9 months to eat, sleep & enjoy my life like a prince. \n\nMy mother used to say I’m a “3 Mahinay Ka Tajir & 9 Mahinay Ka Muhajir”. But if time is money in this busy world .. I’m the Bill Gates of Pakistan !', ''),
(34056, ' @Turumti Bhai cool down yaar i m also on your side.:D and you are absolutely right there was an ex-general (wont take his name as he has passed away). we met him in a duck hunt he told us that he holds a record of chikaras hunted in a single trip and that was around 50 or 60 could''nt remember the right figure. These deers were hunted around 1995.\n\nSo what do you call this?\n\nKaiser Bhai you are saying that a poor farmer pay money for hunting a deer in his land or area whereas an army or any other influentail person comes to his area and not only hunts down several deers but alo enjoys VIP lunchs and dinners by Govt officers.\n\nNo consevation can be done unless the locals get the feeling of owning the area and its habitats or wildlife.', ''),
