(34064, ' Well my dear ... regardless of poor or rich, anyone who does poaching in any form is a poacher by definition ! but like Isaid earlier, with your logic & reasoning you may justify your own definitions. One Wrong Act plus One  Wrong Act will never make Two Rifgt Acts. . or 1 Bad Guy +  1 Bad Guy will never make 2 Good Guys ! So whosoever is poaching is a bad guy and we must condem him  .. whether it''s a General, A Sarkari Afsar or a Wadera !\n\nIf we justify one poor farmer to hunt an Urial for meet in the middle of a nowhere land ... whatsoever, then we''ll have to justify all other poor people of Pakistan to cut off all trees (because the poors need the wood) and shoot all the birds and steal electricity .. and so on ! ... this will become a never ending story !\n\nThe best way to benefit THAT poor man is to make community based hunting conservancies (which are made by ordinary people like You & Me as per the consitution) and generate income from those Urials for the indigenous poors & let them share this income through their own appointed representatives ... this sounds too ideal but it has already happened like a success storey in many conservancies of Pakistan. Where a wadera or even a general cannot even dream of poaching. Simply because those local poors become the rightful owners of those  conservancies. \n\nI wonder if you know that one of Pakistan''s Army Chief (when in power) wanted to hunt a Suleman Markhor in Torghar but he was bluntly refused by the members of STEP (society of torghar environmental protection) who owns the habitat and is responsible for catering legal hunters.', ''),
