(34075, ' [quote=Offroader2323]yes your point is absolutely rght but can you make the same conservancies in Sindh or Baluchistan with out the permission of the local Sardar.\nwildlife dept is under their control and they are MNAs and Ministers so will not allow you to do this.\nsir your Idea is great but have you tried it in Sindh or Baluchistan, and if a local wats to hunt a suleman markhor what will be the discount for him as you have mentioned before that their permit is quite expensive.[/quote]\n\nYes Dear ... the well aware, educated, trained & experienced indigenous people & waderas of many established communities have made it impossible for influential people to poach in their conservancies. But exceptions are always there in our country which is always influenced by currupt elements. \n\nSo tell the most influential General, MNA, MPA or some Minister to try to hunt in the community based conservancies of Durreji or Torghar (in Baluchistan) and/or Halalo, Pachran, Sumbak, Hali Talli (in Jamshoro Sindh) or pose them a challenge to hunt in Tushi, Ghairat (In Chitral) or Kaigha, Tangir in Kohistan (by using any means or method whatsoever)  ... I bet they won''t succeed because these communities have established themselves and have become stong institutions and their indigenous members including their waderas have been educated and they have realised that their future is in conservation of their assets.\n\nBut you are right sir, it happens where the roots of this neewly born system has not taken strength and like any other business or institute,,, this will take some time ... Yet the tug between the right & the wrong, the evil and the good will always stay till Qiyamay ... that''s why God has made the day of judgement for all our deeds !', ''),
