(34147, ' How much did you pay, and where did you get it? Ive seen this for around £350 is that about right?\n\n\nhere s a review I came across\n\n[quote][b]Good Points[/b]: 9 shot mag - excellent reloading - fairly quiet - incredibly easy synthetic stock - great, means im not afraid to carry it around or if i knock it, it dosent scratch.\n\n[b]Bad Points[/b]: Its to easy to load 2 pellets into the barrel at the same time.\n\nGeneral comments: A brilliant air gun! Could shoot a fly off a horses backside from 50 yards! I use logun penetrators (pellets) and they seem to be spot on with this gun. They fly incredibly straight, would recomend them to anyone with an enigma. I do alot of vermin control - mostly squirels, pigeons and rabbits, and this gun allows me to hit and kill 99.9% of everything i shoot. Make sure you get a decent silencer for it. The one that comes with it is rubbish. I have been using a parker hale which is designed for live fire rifles. it is good, but its nothing compared to the logun silencer which makes my gun sound like a light breath of air. All in all, i couldnt be happier with any other airgun.\n[/quote]\n\n\n\nAnyway crongats and enjoy your new gun.', ''),
