(34627, ' Code of Criminal Procedure:\n\nOF ARREST,ESCAPE AND RETAKING\nA—Arrest generally\n46. Arrest how made: (1) In making an arrest the police officer [b]or other person[/b] making\nthe same shall actually touch or confine the body of the person to be arrested, unless\nthere, be a submission to the custody by word or action.\n(2) Restating endeavour to arrest: If such person forcibly resists the ''endeavour to arrest\nhim, or attempts to evade the arrest, such police officer [b]or other-person[/b] may [b]use all\nmeans necessary[/b] to effect the arrest.\n(3) [b]Nothing in this section gives a right to cause the death of a person who is not accused\nof an offence punishable with death or with [imprisonment for life].\n[/b]\n\n59.[b] Arrest by private persons and procedure on such arrest:[/b]\n\n (1) [b]Any private person[/b]\nmay arrest any person who in his view commits a non-bailable and cognizable offence, or\nany proclaimed offender, and without unnecessary delay, shall make over any person so\narrested to a police-officer or, in the absence of a police-officer, take such person or cause\nhim to be taken in custody to the nearest police-station.\n\n\nI believe its self explanatory.. AND an obligation on all of us. The police cannot be everywhere all the time.\nWhy else would you go around toting guns if when you see someone being deprived of honor and property at threat to his life, and you walk away pretending not noticing and call the police which will take upto 20 minutes to reach while the robbers shoot somebody''s  father, son, husband etc.\n\nIt is time all of us stand together and put our foot down on these people.\n\nBesides, even if you shoot them you can surely tell police to take credit for it, I''m sure they''ll be happy to do so. Even if they take money from these gangs, they''re no good dead and will not be owned by anyone.\n\nHowever, please dont go in rambo style, it is better to wait for the opportunity, but when it presents itself, do NOT hesitate!\n\nsounds like hunting doesnt it.. :)', ''),
