(34954, ' Guys why would you want hollow point???  All bullets kill, hollow points were mainly developed in the states to stop over penetration - meaning stop at the terminal target only.  What was and has happened many times is when a cop has shot a criminal the bullet over  penetrates and makes its way through the body and hits someone else.  This ofcourse has meant lawsuits, this was one of the biggest contributing factor where the ammunition manufacturers who are catering to mainly law enforcement agencies developed these types of ammunitions.  The second factor is the sporting aspect such as bowling pin matches.  I have shot at many matches in my day and a standard jacketed round nose ammo would hit the bowling pin and go right through without making the bowling pin fall from the stand.  Hence when I used hollowpoints the pin would litterally fly off the table... having said that don''t anyone assume that the same will happen with humans.  This is Pakistan, and most of us are NOT employed by any LE agency.', ''),
