(35445, ' [quote=Abu Hafs][quote=eminentpk]How about the snub revolver in 0.38sp or 0.357.......they are good manstoppers[/quote]\n\n\nYes I am leaning more and more towards a nice snubie, maybe a taurus like accripone''s.This carried on an ankle holster loaded with .357 hollow points should make for a decent S/D carry gun.What do you think?\n\nIt seems most American "experts" prefer a small revolver for CC as its very reliable and has decent stopping power.[/quote]\n\n\n\nSir jee thats right................I just said that cos i believed that too...... But the revolvers have low capacity you need a good load? or its only how good you are at shooting', ''),
(35446, ' [quote=Conceal Carry][quote=eminentpk]Whats your favorite CCW? and why?\nSmall calibers are easy to conceal but they are less effective\nLarge calibers are hard to conceal but they are more effective[/quote]\n\nIt''s the gun which is hard to conceal, not the caliber. There are a number of 45 caliber guns designed specifically for CC, the only drawback is that because of the smaller grip of CC guns the mag capacity for the larger .45 round is reduced.[/quote]\n \n\nYup buddy you are right..... thats why i always have this question...... one should have a man stopper or a more bullets in the gun.....', ''),
(35447, ' [quote=Enigmatic Desires][quote=Abu Hafs][quote=eminentpk]How about the snub revolver in 0.38sp or 0.357.......they are good manstoppers[/quote]\n\n\nYes I am leaning more and more towards a nice snubie, maybe a taurus like accripone''s.This carried on an ankle holster loaded with .357 hollow points should make for a decent S/D carry gun.What do you think?\n\nIt seems most American "experts" prefer a small revolver for CC as its very reliable and has decent stopping power.[/quote]\n\nsmall barrel .357 revolvers cant usualy get the full terminal ballastics of their 4 an 6 inch counter parts. the bullet simply does''nt have enough barrel to hit full vilocity.. unless spacial smal barrel ammo (such as hte kind offered by speer dot) is used.. additionaly the huge muzzal blast an high recoil can be a bit of a bummer. apart from that. snubbies are fat. as compared to their pistolcounter parts\n\n\nI rather like CC''s choice.. the mac is smal relieabl an tough. the russians may not have teh wide veriety of amarican weapons.. but the few designs tehy do have . are pretty tough..[/quote]\n\nOk we have the votes for Makarov.....Conceal Carry bhai....you seem too be consolidating the choice for the best CCW', ''),
