(35552, ' Gentlemen, \n\nFor 62 years we have simply passed by and acted as if nothing has happened. Which is why today, collectively, we find ourselves in the morass that we are in. Frankly, I think we are the most selfish people on the planet. True we may get into trouble for helping others, but could you live with yourself, for not helping save someone''s honour, life and property - and see a girl being abducted and subsequently raped by criminals, see a child being shot infront of his mother''s eyes, see a poor man losing his life saving to a couple of armed robbers? If you can, you are very lucky indeed. You are not burdened with a conscience. \n\nBut then I wonder why history does not remember the millions who chose to pass by as if nothing happened, but rather the handful who hailed the call of their conscience.', ''),
