(35603, ' The whole point of conceal carry is to carry it [i]concealed[/i]. If company policy forbids carry of firearms in the office, even a law-abiding, gun-carrying fellow will have to abide by the rules. If the policy is silent in this matter, it is best to carry your gun in a way which does not shout [i]"Look at me, I have a GUN!!!"[/i].\n\nIf there is no company policy regarding firearms, a guy carrying cannot and should not be persecuted, as he is abiding by the law. However, if rules expressly forbid carry, the guy should be ready to face whatever punishment the managers throw at him, as he was in the wrong.\n\nPersonally, I believe that the right to self-defence belongs to each and every person, and no govt, company, management, etc, should attempt to remove this right of ours.', ''),
