(35638, ' [quote=Adeel Ahmad][quote=Abu Hafs]A modern reproduction of a medieval weapon \n\n\n[img]http://www.talismancrossbows.co.uk/images/crossbows/angel_img.jpg[/img]\n\n\n\n[b]Length:                           42" - 46"[/b]\n\n[b]Width:                             31"[/b]\n\n[b]Depth:                             7"[/b]\n\n[b]Weight:                          -9lb[/b]\n\n[b]DrawWeight:                   70lb/240lb[/b]\n\n[b]Power Stroke:                 8"[/b]\n\n[b]Feet per sec:                   360 +fps[/b]\n\n[b]Materials:Alloy, Brass & Walnut[/b][/quote]\nI dont care if its the modern medieval weapon or a modern version of the medieval weapon but i like it a lot. Does anyone know about availability and price.[/quote]\n\n\n\nI just phoned the gentleman who makes these beautiful crossbows to get more information about them.He was very helpful and seemed like a a genuinely sincere person.\n\nHe told me that the one in the picture is handmade and it took him 3 months to make,he quoted me a figure of £3000 for it. I told him that I''d posted a picture of it on a Pakistani gun enthusiasts forum and was receiving a lot of interest from the members.\n\nHe said he makes these crossbows to order but could make \n cheaper versions for hunting/target practice etc on request.\n\nThe one in the picture could be used for hunting at a range of about 60 yards and at that distance the arrow would likely pass straight through  medium sized game if the right broad head (arrow tip) is used.\n\nThere are commercially available crossbows  that are good for hunting etc but they do not look anywhere as nice as the handmade one above.\n\nThis site is one of the main dealers in the U.K\n\n[url]http://www.crossbows4u.co.uk/#[/url]\n\n\nThis is one of the top models \n\n[url]http://www.crossbows4u.co.uk/#/stryker/4528291188[/url]\n\n\n\nThere are also many videos on youtube of people hunting with crossbows.\n\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qt6pTEwEs9A[/url]', ''),
