(35653, ' [quote=MOLAjat]Can rifle be used for SD/HD. I have a .303 rifle of my father with me. Someone told me that the rounds are too powerful for short range and can pass through the wall. I have never seen someone keeping a rifle in car except AK 47 which a common man like me cannot afford.[/quote]\n\n\n\nMy 2 cents worth!\n\nSir, spraying high vilocity bullets in an urban enviroment is just plain criminal. The ak/47 is a military fire arm designed to be little better then a meat grinder.. Incidentaly the same holds true for the .303 as well.. \n a long range battle rifle suitable for trench warfare such as the kind seen in the 1st world war.. \n\nShot guns are great for HD.. I have one too.. but for SD.. again. carrying it around is not usualy an option..  As i found out to my detriment a few days ago.. when i was in a potentialy hostile situation an my shot gun was at home.. \n\nIf u have to go for only 1 weapon for both hd/sd.. An hav no prior expereince wiht fire arms.. what soever.. and are not used to shooting. then your best bet would be a revolver. simple reliable an robust.. and of course inexpensive  preferbly a 6 to 8 shot .32 or higher calibre.', ''),
