(35663, ' [quote=Conceal Carry][quote=Enigmatic Desires][quote=Conceal Carry]\n\nI have never fired a real CZ hence can''t really compare the recoil, but common sense, third law of motion and this simple equatin m1v1=m2v2 do point in the same direction you are referring to. Having said that polymer frams are known to dampen the recoil as compared to in full metal frames.\n\nMy personal experience: I find it manageable.[/quote]\n\nFor me recoil has always been an issue wiht hand guns.. partly cause the 1st time i ever fired a hand gun.. it damed near flew out of my hand!!\n\nBut if u do find it managable... alls well.. In my case.. i would prefersomethng heavier.. the original czechoslovak cz75 was built like a rock.. i saw a used an beat up one in a shop in karachi..it was selling wel into  6 figures[/quote]\n\n\nJust saw today a cz75 (note CZ75B, which is newer version) in fair condition with hogue grips, asking 80K non negotiated. Had it been a CZ75B, i would have been posting it''s pics right now.[/quote]\n\n\nIn karachi? good condition wiht hogue grips.. WOW.. thats waay lower tehn the prices I have seen..', ''),
