(35859, ' [quote=Turumti]Senor 12 Gauge, \n\nDo you think Hatsan Escort Magnum or Baikal MP153 is a better choice for quail and duck shoots in Sindh? Keeping in mind that at least 200 cartridges are fired in about an hour, and you need a gun, that is not only well balanced but also produces a good pattern and is reliable too.\n\nI find the Escort well balanced but I have concerns about its reliability. On the other hand the Baikal is reputedly a rock, but unfortunately, I find it balanced like one as well, And I have not heard many good things about its pattern.\n\nThanking you in anticipation, of your insightful repsonse.[/quote]\n\n\nbrother, I agree on the pattern part, infact if u read my earlier posts on the subject i''ve admitted openly that Baikal''s patterns can be questioned, allow me to quote myself:\n\n[quote]as far as pattern is concerned, it can be improved by buying after-market choke tubes, as far as load sensitivity is concerned, it can be cured by properly breaking-in the gun. Russians take weapon durability very seriously, there is a reason why Baikal mp153 was "russia''s 100 best exports" and was "guns and ammo" gun of the year and was "shooting times" gun of the year.[/quote]\n\ni''m afraid that i might have conveyed a wrong message above, when i said their patterns can be improved, in reality their pattern are absolutely are absolultey fine in more open chokes, its the performance of their tighther chokes (full, extra full) that is not upto standard. so, if u''r gonna use it for any type of hunt that requires more open chokes, their patterns should be fine. otherwise like i''ve recommended before, buy aftermarket choke tubes (carslons, clonial, trulock).\n\nthink for a second, u can improve the patterns of Baikal by buying aftermarket chokes which cost less than 1500 rupees each (shipping, handling and duty paid) but how will u improve the reliability of a turkish shotgun (I dont see a quick solution to that problem).\n\nRegards.\n\n\np.s. Russian vs Turkish = Russian wins hand down.', ''),
(35860, ' [quote=Enigmatic Desires]The cougar has a rotating barrel that helps in eliminating muzzle flip repeat target acquisition.\n[/quote]\n\n\nWrong. A rotating barrel mechanim is to lock the slide momentarily so that it does not cycle untill the pressure of expanding gases has fallen to a level at which the slide can safely cycle without breaking off the frame.', ''),
