(35865, ' profile of a HP bullet matters alot as all we want is reliable feeding in an SD pistol. not all HPs are of same shape. some are more flattened, some have a bigger nose, some have smaller nose... same HP may work flawlessly in one pistol whereas it may not work that much reliable in other. profiles of HPs matter because of the fitting on the magazine and the angle at which it presents a bullet to the throat of chamber, and also angle and finish of the feed ramp is yet the most important factor here. a good pistol will eat all HPs but a normal pistol will work with HPs which have a profile more like an FMJ. cuz an FMJ/round nose/ball bullet tends to work in almost all pistols reliably.', ''),
