(36012, ' A very informative discussion is going on here. In my opinion all the members have picked the right cause of the malfunction and that is the ammo. Mr. CC have listed all the possible causes of a weaker bang. Had there been a full bang there could have been a greater damage to the slide and a nasty recoil of the pistol as full energy must have released backward. I have seen a that kind of accident at LRC and the guy involved was a medalist shooter Mr Raza Tarin(whom ABBAS bought Rugger) and the gun was Glock. Whenever there is a weak bang we find a lot of unburnt gunpowder in chamber and slide, mostly shell dosen''t get ejected(due to the lack of power) and pallet stuck in the barrel(due to lack of power).\nIf the ammo go off with full force then there can be wrong diameter projectile or way too accessive jammed barrel to create a such result of stuck projectile. Beleive me, this kind of situation seldom go without damaging the gun.\n\nNow few words about the TAURUS, i really feel odd when i see so many bad reviews about this gun. Fortunately my experience with Taurus is completely different. Besides Glock 17 i have PT92 and 24/7. My PT92 is the gun of my choice on range, have fired more than 3000 rounds (Chinese and POF)since i have bought this gun and have never came across a single FTF or FTE. A friend of mine Mr MUNIR a senior member on our forum, an experienced shooter also have the same experience. Mr Munir won Silver medal in big bore shooting this year and the gun he used was a PT92. My 24/7 do FTF but the frequency is not more than 2%.', ''),
