(36045, ' [quote=Adeel Ahmad]Seems like i have opened a Pandora''s Box which is turning out to be extremely good discussion.\n@Glocky\nI dont consider the original Russian Luger to be bad ammo as such thing has never happened to my 24/7 or any of my friend''s using that ammo. This is not a normal case that might be related to FTF or FTE, its a case where shell was ejected while the bullet was stuck half way of the barrel and complete gun powder was burned inside the Pistol. Bad Ammo, i dont think so here. Its bad Manufacturing by Taurus. I dont that with so much power provided by the gun powder, a bullet should ever be lodged like that halfway through the barrell.[/quote]\n\nMate while i am no fan of Taurus firearms. This is purely and simply an ammo fault. I never referred it to being a FTF or FTE, rather the round is a squib. Please read up on it before making up your mind. It can happen with any weapon and any ammo. I don''t know what Russain 9mm ammo you get but the one i have used in Kar has always been a disappointment and has resulted in FTFs and FTEs in many firearms that i used it in. I still stand by what i say.', ''),
