(36054, ' [quote=TAREEN]Adeel Bhai I was referring to the black Taurus that was being fired by our guest at the range while we were tuning our rifles''  sights & you were shooting with your Glock. There were 2 or 3 FTF & FTE issues as I remember. Being a handgun enthusiast, I thought u might have taken a deeper interest in that issue than me.[/quote]\nTareen Bhai i did notice everything that went wrong with Taurus 24/7 but i was thinking about mentioning it in a new topic as this debate is becoming very informative.\n\n@Glocky\nI did read your post thoroughly and never said that you mentioned FTF/FTE, it was just a general thing. CC has clearly mentioned something that i was also thinking about but the whole point of this situation is to rate the 609 Ti. I have used my 24/7 very extensively and sometimes with crap ammo but just like HJ, my failure rate would also be around 2-3%. This scenario is a whole new level a bad and i do know that it does not matter which weapon you are using, something that can go wrong will go wrong. We are concluding here from the discussion that it was an ammo fault. I will also agree with everyone that it was an ammo fault but what about the bad reviews all over that Polymer series is getting. I have not seen a single bad review about 92/99 and i do swear by it any time. If given a choice, i would rate Beretta 92FS and Taurus PT 92 almost. Ammo is at fault and that is the conclusion here by everyone but is Taurus also at Fault?', ''),
