(36161, ' during inspection firing of different lots from 1991- 2006 of POF 9mm for army, some expert from POF once told me that all bullets expand immediatly on firing due to high temp produced in the chamber ... one the characteristic of a good ammo apart from counted grains and good primers is that they also have a constant size of expansion, which ever lot you may fire, where as this is one of the maj reason because of which darra made rounds spoils the barrel.... ive not fired luger except for a dozen or 2 but as for POF 9mm which ive fired in ten ov thousands. In my record it has never stuck up in the barrel, be it any hand gun or an MP-5\nApart from ever blamed taurus, luger bullet may also have a role to play in it ..... this never happens in the fresh lots of POF ammo but i have seen it happening twice in 5yrs in practice ammo of MG1A3 and on repeated inspection the ammo was to be blamed because the lot from early 80s was slightly damped (only visible under magnified glass) this effects expansion of bullet and also result in low propellant burning.', ''),
