(36178, ' [quote=Denovo87][quote=Dr Zakir]I think this is quite  a mature forum and any body visiting the forum will agree that here people are talking about guns within the law . We do not discuss PB weapons which is quote an attraction to general public and younger generation. No body here wants to buy a weapon without lisence hazards of ariel fireing , carrying in car and taking to office are discussed which would be very informative not only to us but to any age group . Moderators are there to check any childish political religious vulgar talk and they are doing an excellent job. And every body should learn that firearms is no  joke and while we are discussing it we are very seriuos about it[/quote]\n\n+1, I second it. PG forum is to teach people to play safe with guns, restricting it to a limited community will not serve the purpose. If a younger gun enthusiast is restricted to get a membership or entrance, its like restricting him to learn true gun ethics.\nAnd as long as our mods are there we should not worry about any one behaving childish, vulgar or outlaw on this forum.[/quote]\nI raised a concern that some young people might be getting involved in this forum and i never mentioned that any such thing is being shown here. I do not agree with you that a young enthusiast should be allowed here as if we were to give guns in hands of young people then there would not be age limit of 21.', ''),
