(36236, ' [quote=Denovo87][quote=topak]just a question...\nif .22 is not effective for HD/SD what was the purpose to make it ?[/quote]\nHunting bigger birds & smaller animals.[/quote]\nWell in my opinion, not all the calibers are meant for a single purpose. I agree with Denovo,\nbesides big birds n small animals, it''s meant for target practice and fun shooting. Regarding\nit''s use for SD, I don''t say it would be ineffective. If used properly, even a slingshot or a knife\ncan be effective for SD, but one can''t call these suitable SD weapons.', ''),
(36239, 'Opinion on Fiber Optic Beads for Shotguns somebody asked me today the importance of Fiberoptic beads in hunting and sports use. I prefer them, infact cant do much without them, reason being that they make pointing the gun easier for me especially in low light conditions.\n\nmy all purpose fiberoptic bead''s diameter is 3mm (any thicker and it bothers me, have used 3.5mm too by the way) and length around 2 inches (the more the merrier)\n\nthis one attaches itself onto the shotgun rib using magnetic buttons in the bottom base, no need to remove original brass bead\n[img]http://www.ableammo.com/catalog/images/ssi/sm/89433.jpg[/img]\n\nthis one just snaps onto regular plain barrel, again no need to remove original/factory brass bead \n[img]http://www.impactguns.com/store/media/hiviz/hiviz_89402_sm.jpg[/img]\n\nfor some people it seems fiber optic beads promotes quick target acquisition, improves shotgun mount (u''ll have to be dead center on the gun/rib to get full bright bead), reduces master/dominent eye conflict, aids in low light conditions (specially in dusk and dawn) and helps u in aiming at the moving target with both eyes open (big plus as with both eyes open u dont lose depth perception).\n\nand for some, its plain nuisance as it takes attention away from the target and towards the bead itself, it obstructs the target and most importantly just doesnt go with the traditionalism associated with a fine shotgun.\n\nso lets hear it out guyz, where do u stand?\n\nu stand with the PRO FIBER OPTIC BEAD CROWD or ANTI FIBER OPTIC BEAD CROWD and mostly importantly why?\n\nRegards', ''),
