(36343, ' [quote=tarzen81]@All . . . :) Well i think safety should be revealed to the ones who actually use it. Rather then developing passion of fire arm to the young lot and due to the curiosity they will hurt themselves...[/quote]\nNow this is something that everyone should look into. I mean reading everything that is available on this forum might make younger people learn a few things but does it not create a craving to have such weapons in your hand which are being dicussed all over the forum. I mean younger lot might not get something from your permission but what if they got it without your permission.\nAll learning aside, if lets say a 17 year old teen ager went hay wire just after playing Max Payne and killed 7 class fellows in America, God forbid if something of the sort happened in Pakistan, we cannot begin to imagine how much this is going to hurt Pak Guns.\nIf some one''s son was under legal age and after being very active on this forum, he would do something rash, i think we would be facing many legal difficulties.\nPlease dont think according to being a Pakistani as here we place 5 year old in front seat while in most countries its illegal. Please look into the legal merits of this thing which are already haunting this forum.\nSeriously guys, involving 5 and 7 year old children is not safe according to my opinion.', ''),
(36344, ' Its always the MAN behind the GUN. Know someone who took on 3 neighbourhood thugs with an old single barrel shotgun. The Foes were armed with AK & pump actions. While this person had this single barrel with a couple of shells in hand & 2 in the teeth. He fired 3 shots with amazing speed & made all the 3 run away with  2 injured. Obviously he was well versed in using his single barrel but when asked he says GOD was on his side & he somehow found all the courage.', ''),
(36345, ' Jams can an do occur in virtualy all weapons.. \n\nWHy does the Taurus get the blame?\n\nPartly cause its a very popular brand in Pakistan.. \n\nMost people cant afford the Berettas and S&Ws an the Glocks. While Turkish/Chinese offerings are also increasing in popularity. But I have yet to see any hand gun retailer not stocking Taurus weapons. U cant help not running into em. Apart from the ubiquitous ''TT'' .. Taurses are quite simply "In"', ''),
