(36385, ' I would humbly disagree with the above proposition.\n\nPak Guns and Max Payne. hardly any similarity exists. \n\nNothing contained in this forum is in any way providing a stimulus for a child to go on a shooting rampage.\n\nKnowledge of guns is a very important thing, and shooting is a love learnt very early in life. Kids should be taught gun safety and shooting early in their life. but always supervised. This has the added benefit of quelching their curiosity.\n\nHave you ever seen those who never shot as a kid, and they scrounge money to buy a "17000 ka baratta" which they carry mexican style? THAT is the dangerous type.\n\nNone of the international forums are age restricted. and if somebody had gone shooting after reading how to clean your bore and other technical information regarding weapon handling, it would have happened by now. \n\nLastly, Pakistani kids arent half as psychopathic as their western contemporaries due to greater family and social bonds. Just like there are no serial killers and serial rapists here (one or two dont really count)\n\nOur society is suffocated and paranoid enough already. Let us not make it more so.  \n\nAagay aapp ki merzi.. \n:/', ''),
