(36391, ' People, Multan members had another GTG on Wednesday and i thank all the members for being kind enough to travel to my friend''s farm for some fun. We enjoyed a lot there with all the oldies :) huffing and pufing due to heat.\nHere are some pictures to go with it.\n\nSo on the Left is Tareen Bahi, Middle Ahmad Bhai and Right is Mustanir Bhai.\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img31.imageshack.us/img31/9526/40627391.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nMustanir Bhai was looking a bit shy in the previous picture but man he looks in full bloom here. On extreme right is a guest of Ahmad Bhai\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img190.imageshack.us/img190/2339/35999463.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nBoth the master hunters settings themselves up to have a go at, The Wall People and i mean it The Wall:)\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img189.imageshack.us/img189/5713/74781482.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nMustanir Bhai has had it with it and finally decided to stop firing while both Mashood Bhai and his Guest are amused at the situation\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img43.imageshack.us/img43/3048/11386177.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nTareen Bhai is still going strong and he went strong till the end.\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img197.imageshack.us/img197/1131/49844774.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nAhmad Bhai is wondering as to what should he do now that he has smoked some cigarettes. :)\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img40.imageshack.us/img40/4109/14711197.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nThe lone ranger\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img16.imageshack.us/img16/4665/68397218.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nLook who decided to join Tareen Bhai\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img195.imageshack.us/img195/8090/70228948.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nAnd some joyous noises were heard because Tareen Bhai was finally able to adjust the Scope.\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img38.imageshack.us/img38/3875/23510700.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nMustanir Bahi was kind enough to hunt a bird for us but i already made dinner reservations somewhere else.\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img269.imageshack.us/img269/4585/10509595.jpg[/img][/url]\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img189.imageshack.us/img189/1157/56789860.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nAnd finally i killed something :cool: using Laser Pointer of my G22 as it was dark then.\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img189.imageshack.us/img189/7629/94455348.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nSo guys here is the story of Second GTG by Multan members. I would have certainly taken some pictures during dinner but i too was hungry like the rest to even bother :lol:\n\nAs far as my picture is concerned, people security reasons, you can understand being a Bachelor and all. :D', ''),
(36392, ' Thanks for th welcome guys.\n\nI think we have too many regulations concerning firearms, but it is much better here than some other places. We can own as many firearms as we want. I live in a rural area and everyone has firearms.\n\nWe can own handguns, but are only allowed to use them at a range. No hunting or carry while hunting. All firearms must be registered, both handguns and long guns. We are trying to do away with the long gun registry, but it is a struggle.\n\nWe can use any type of long gun for hunting except Assault rifles such as the AR15. We can use semi auto as long as it is not an AR configuration. Rifles and shotguns are permitted depending on the species hunted. I''m fortunate to live in Alberta as we have a wide variety of game to hunt and a great deal of land to access.\nI have access to several million acres of both private and public land.\n\nI use a 60 gr bullet in my Swift for the wolves, and a 52 gr. Sierra hp match in my .223 for coyotes. The wolves weigh about 50-60 kg and the coyote weighs in at about 15-20 kg.\n\nWe have lots of bears as well both black and grizzly.', ''),
(36393, ' teh vendor of the 24/7 told me that under so circumstance am I supposed to dry fire it.. \n\nANd it went for all striker fired weapons w/o hammers. how ever he was ambivalent towards hand guns with hammers..', ''),
(36394, ' There''s nothing special, its what suits you the best. Polymer pistols are lighter hence easier to carry and shoot. That in no way means that its a superior pistol. Not at all. Both metal and polymer firearms have their pros and cons. Its what works for your system.  \n\nOne problem with polymer pistols is that they lack character unlike metal guns, hence the popular western term tupperware :)\n\nFor me reliability is the foremost factor in choosing a firearm. No compromise. Period', ''),
(36395, ' [quote=ay_be_why]@12G, sir please shed some light on this issue:\n\nI came across this thread at PakWheels regarding the performance of ZIC oils after reading your cleaner/ lube formula. Apparently, some users are not satisfied by the current performance/quality of ZIC lubricants. They fear that ZIC has either dropped the quality of their products or "DO NUMBER" ZIC products are being sold in the market. If there is really some problem with the quality of these oils, how will it affect the performance of the lube that you have formed? or since a firearm isn''t subject to the workload like that of an engine, so the lube will work anyway?? please elaborate.\n\n[url]http://www.pakwheels.com/forumreply_az_TopicID!71787~ForumID!10~pw.html[/url]\n\nThanks[/quote]\n\nincase ZIC has dropped the quality of their lubricants, we are stuck on square one. however if u buy their products from any reputable dealer i''m sure he will not sell "do-number" products to you for the sake of company''s or his own''s name.\n\none more thing: u can subsitute ZIC ATF with GSOIL DEX3 safely, as they are both ATF and if i remember correctly both had almost same lubrication properties. just contacted director at ZIC oil Mr. Tahir Azam, he denies any quality change by the company in ZIC XQ (the one i used in my formula). so, i guess we are good here\n\nif u cant find ''em, just subsititute it for any motor oil that contains PAO''s (polyalphaolefins) such as Mobil 1 (5w40 or 0W40) or KIXX PAO 0W40 by GSOIL\n\nRegards', ''),
(36396, ' [quote=Glocky]There''s nothing special, its what suits you the best. Polymer pistols are lighter hence easier to carry and shoot. That in no way means that its a superior pistol. Not at all. Both metal and polymer firearms have their pros and cons. Its what works for your system.  \n\nOne problem with polymer pistols is that they lack character unlike metal guns, hence the popular western term tupperware :)\n\nFor me reliability is the foremost factor in choosing a firearm. No compromise. Period[/quote]\n\n\nYes. i have heard that Glocks are the most reliable hand guns in the world. \n\nBut does''nt the lack of weight eliminate that crucial ''feel'' that a combat shooter has to have in his weapon to have confidence in it. \n\n2ndly doesn''t the lack of weight increase its recoil? (acting on the assumption the lighter the weapon the more it wil be susceptible to muzzle flip)', ''),
(36397, ' Thanks Sialvi. I like the Ruger #1. I have other calibers that I use for big game. These two are my predator calling rifles. \n\nI am not a farmer but I live in a rural area . I have several horses that I use for hunting in the mountains so I have a farm of 160 acres. I think that is about 70 hectares.\n The area is made up of cattle ranches and farms. The predators can be destructive to the livestock in the spring when the young are being born. It makes  for lots of area to hunt.', ''),
