(36624, ' I do not do my own taxidermy. i have a friend who is an artist in that field. I do not even tell him what I want done. I give him the hide and he decides what to do with it. I''ve never been disappointed in his work. He lives in the U.S. We barte for his work. i supply guided hunts for him and he does my taxidermy.:D\n\nOver the years I have shot many bears.[50=] Years ago I sold the pelts. The fur market has gradually shrunk so I don''t sell pelts now.\n\nWe have a bear season in the spring and in the fall. We have a two bear bag limit per hunter. I no longer hunt grizzly bears. They are in Alberta but the hunting is by draw. and each year it harder to draw a permit. I did hunt them when I was younger,but it is a young man''s game because of the terrain where they live.\n\nI do hunt black bears. We have about 30% color phase bears. They range in color form blond through brown, cinnamon, and  black. A good bear will be 2 meters from nose to tail.\n\nI use calls to hunt them. I set up on the ground in my ghillie suit and use animal distress sounds to call them in. Fawn distress or cub bear sounds are effective. We can call them into bow range. It is quite exciting.:D\n\nI use a Ruger #1 single shot in a 7mm Remington  magnum for bears. 160 gr. Nosler partition bullets. It kills them graveyard dead right there. We take the pelt for a rug or mount and we eat the meat. \nI have also shot bears with a Ruger #1 in a 25.06. It will kill them, but does not kill with the authority of the 7mag.', ''),
(36625, ' [quote=Redfrog] We take the pelt for a rug or mount and we eat the meat. \n[/quote]\n\n\nThanks for the info Redfrog, I never realised that people actually eat bear meat, that''s the first Ive heard of it.', ''),
(36626, ' [quote=SAJJAD ALI]in HD & SD the aim is not to kill the other person But the main aim is to harras it and in very rare cases we used to shoot them direct.[/quote]\n\n\nSorry bro I disagree with your assertion that the main aim in a defensive situation would be to merely harass an assailant. If someone threatens my life or that of a loved one or enters my home armed with bad intentions, I''m gonna want to stop him dead in his tracks whatever that takes.', ''),
(36627, ' I agree with Sajjad. Plz don''t kill if u can harass away a bandit. Legal proceedings in a purely SD case are daunting.', ''),
(36628, ' Toverish means companion :D ahem ahem its one of the international languages i know well', ''),
(36629, ' Some people only take the pelt, but many hunt just for the meat. It is exellent eating.\n\nI have served  a bear roast to dinner guests who are neither hunters nor people who eat game meat.  They thought it was roast beef, and simply would not believe it was bear. Of course i told them when we had finished the meal and they thought I was joking.\n\nIt is slightly darker and coarser grained than beef, but flavor wise is very close. \n\nEvery country has some unusual stuff that is eaten. It is no different here. I''ve eaten soem unusual things.:D', ''),
(36630, ' really we''r going to learn many things new from u Redfrog. wolves or coyotes r also eaten or not?', ''),
