(36655, ' [quote=Conceal Carry]I''m amazed at the casualness of remarks made by certain mmembers. The committee finally decided to fire the person, primarily not for carrying despite company policy not to carry in the office premises, but because it was intended to threaten a colleague who discovered some misppropriations from the funds. This was exactly what I feared and had mentioned in one of my earlier post.[/quote]\n\nSo he was fired not because he carried a gun to the work place but for his intention for carrying it. \nTo my opinion this exactly is how it should be dealt like, a warning is enough for simply carrying a weapon to work but authorities must look into the intention & most importantly character/personality of the accused person if he/she carried it with a purpose an extreme measure is must. A casual carrier is no problem to society and his/her co-workers, he/she should always been given a 2nd chance or even should be provided a place to keep his/her weapon safely during work hours (if he doesnot already have a car or locked drawer to keep it). That is my aproach being a pakgunner.', ''),
