(36665, ' [quote=MHMalik]@ Tareen, sir which rifle and which scope? Also did you buy the barrel rest or got it made?[/quote]\nAs Adeel Ahmad already replied, the rifle is an Armscor series 1400 bolt-action (22lr) bought for Rs. 24k from Lahore and the scope is Chinese make 3-12x40 bought from Abbotabad for Rs. 4.5k.\n\n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img16.imageshack.us/img16/2273/22343434.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nAnd the gun rest was made by an upholstery maker as per my requirement. This saddle is made to be strapped to the roll-cage of hunting vehicle and makes an excellent rest for rifle for long shots or smaller targets. Can also be spread on flat surface when needed and helps to avoid damage to the gun as well as polished surface underneath (if any).\n \n[url=http://www.postimage.org/][img]http://img29.imageshack.us/img29/2603/78547942.jpg[/img][/url]', ''),
