(163442, ' ADEEL AHMAD and SIALVI \nValue able information. It is a P17 Remington Rifle. The 8 x 57 was stamped later at DARRA as 8x57 was a German Cartridge and not American.\n8X 57 military surplus ammo was and still is lying in abundance in Darra so this rifle was stamped as an 8x57. I am not sure whether it was re-barreled; in all probability the bore was enlarged from .300 to .315 to shoot  the .323 bullets with out excessive presures. This was done by using bits in hook cutting devices employed usually in Darra, I have seen M1 Garrands also similarly converted to 8X57 from 30-06.', ''),
