(36714, ' [quote=Dr Zakir]i would like the input of fellow pakgunners about their opinion for best calibre for HD / SD , 9mm , .45 ,.357 mag , .40 , 10 mm, .30 , .357 sig . \nalso kindly check the link [url=http://www.freerepublic.com/focus/news/849728/posts]www.freerepublic.com/focus/news/849728/posts[/url][/quote]\n\nalso the chart represented here is calculating percentages in terms of averages. .44 magnum ecountered 9 dead out of 10 of total recorded stats makes it 90% effective. when compared to other calibers like 9mm total stats are around 500 shootings where 150 were stopped on single shot. \nill be advocating Shot Placement as crucial.. and caliber size as make up', ''),
(36715, ' Ahhh!!! A debate after my own heart... \n\nThese days even the BGs are gradualy shifting to 9mms. how the power an efficiency of the .30 round is truely awesome.. \n\ni personaly saw a man shot dead by a .30. Infact in most cases of street violence in Pakistan hadly any1 survives being shot by the .30.\n\nThe drawback of the .30 is that by an large only ball ammo is available. unlike the 9mm and barring the TT very few handguns are offered in this calibre.\n\nNow however, our desi artisans are offering 92 F clones in .30 as well.. i saw a wel made gun at famous arms in karachi.. made by afridi arms.. costing 24K. Its 9mm counterpart was worth 22k..\nGiven a choice in an SD situation. I would not consider mysef at a disadvantage if I were armed wiht  the .30', ''),
