(36852, ' [quote=Enigmatic Desires][quote=MOLAjat]Can rifle be used for SD/HD. I have a .303 rifle of my father with me. Someone told me that the rounds are too powerful for short range and can pass through the wall. I have never seen someone keeping a rifle in car except AK 47 which a common man like me cannot afford.[/quote]\n\n\n\nMy 2 cents worth!\n\nSir, spraying high vilocity bullets in an urban enviroment is just plain criminal. The ak/47 is a military fire arm designed to be little better then a meat grinder.. Incidentaly the same holds true for the .303 as well.. \n a long range battle rifle suitable for trench warfare such as the kind seen in the 1st world war.. \n\nShot guns are great for HD.. I have one too.. but for SD.. again. carrying it around is not usualy an option..  As i found out to my detriment a few days ago.. when i was in a potentialy hostile situation an my shot gun was at home.. \n\nIf u have to go for only 1 weapon for both hd/sd.. An hav no prior expereince wiht fire arms.. what soever.. and are not used to shooting. then your best bet would be a revolver. simple reliable an robust.. and of course inexpensive  preferbly a 6 to 8 shot .32 or higher calibre.[/quote]\n\n\n+1, nothing beats a 12 bore for HD. For SD (CC) a compact pistol should be first option.', ''),
(36853, ' Guys recoil spring is not only one Reason of gun jam\nthere are many other reasons\n1.it may be rounds problum (local rounds may be reason of jam)\n2.Magazines will cause jams when they get old, bent etc\n3.if Magazines spring too tight\n4.ejector failed\n5.Handgun  dirty or too much oil/lube (Too much oil/lube will do more to screw things up)', ''),
