(36928, ' I use a ghillie a lot in calling predators. I have had coyotes to within one metre while I was in a ghillie.\nThe ghillies in the video are very effective, but not user friendly. They are heavy and hot.and prone to snag on underbrush.\n\nThey are designed for maximum concealment required for the military in a conflict environment.\n\nThe ghillie I use is not intended to make me invisible. It is simply intended to change my profile so I lose my "human" form.\n\nMy suit is a commercially produced ghillie. It is a mash undergarment with camo strips sewn to it. With the mesh it is lightweight and it breathes so it is not uncomfortable in the heat of early season. \n\nDuring season we call our first stand at dawn and our last at sunset. In between we may do 12 stands some a few miles apart. We drive from one to the next. I put my ghillie on at dawn, hunt and drive with it on and take it off after our last stand. It is that comfortable to use. As a result it does get used instead of left behind.\n\nHere are some pics.\n\n[img]http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v50/Redfrog/P1010006b.jpg[/img]\nFrom 50 meters\n[img]http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v50/Redfrog/CopyofP1010001.jpg[/img]\n\n[img]http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v50/Redfrog/P1010006.jpg[/img]\n\nTwo men at 30 meters\n[img]http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v50/Redfrog/P1010004.jpg[/img]\n\n\nI have seen some outstanding things though the mask of my ghillie:D', ''),
