(37036, ' @9mm\nI am a big fan of Taurus and this thread was not started just to bash Taurus but in fact to get opinions from everyone about this problem. I have used Taurus very extensively and after quite a lot of failure with Polymer versions i have decided to stay away from it. If i had to make a choice of buying Beretta 92FS or Taurus PT92, i would go for Taurus PT92 in the blink of any eye because of its reliability. I have fed Luger, POF, Chinese, Dara and every kind of crap bullet through my G26 without even a single issue. Such Taurus models on the other hand are turning out to be Ammo sensitive and that is just it. I cannot say if its bad manufacturing or any fault of the Pistol but the fault is there. Its the Ammo sensitivity of Polymer models which i dont like and have made me stay away from them.', ''),
