(37046, ' [quote=Bullseye]Wow,  I guess this is a Taurus Bashing thread. I would like to share my experience here as well. I own a 24/7 Millennium Pro for a couple of years now and have abused it to the full extent of the term. Well, maybe I am just lucky but my baby has not let me down once. In fact I might go for a second Taurus next week. I would have opted for a glock or a Baretta or HK, if they were in my budget, but for its price I guess Taurus is not a bad weapon. But then again thats my opinion.\n\nCheers[/quote]\nI used his weapon on the range and just to pull his a leg a little, i collected few duds from ground and loaded it in his millennium. Intention was to give Dear Sir Bullseye a scare. But i was astonished when all rounds were fired in first try and no mis / hang / dud fire was experienced.\nSo not all Taurus products are bad.', ''),
