(37159, ' @ay_be_why\n\nDSA is a good and a reliable firearm. however since ur looking for a utilitarian type combination, I would recommend get ur self a Hatsan Escort Combo, short barrel for HD and long barrel for Hunting. DSA however is good enough for HD and I dont see a better gun for that single purpose (benefit to cost ratio wise)\n\nOne more thing u can do, get DSA with additional long barrel for occassional hunting, not a perfect tool for the job but it''ll get the job done respectfully, atleast. once u develop the feel for a shotgun/hunting/skeet, u can move up to Hatsan Escort combo or an even better shotgun.\n\nSome people might not agree to this part:\n\nI believe that a person should always start from the bottom and move up the ladder inorder to fully respect and enjoy any tool. an example would be to start with Mehran before jumping onto a Honda Civic. one cannot fully appreciate and understand/value the luxuries a Civic can offer without (as a contrast) experiencing a Mehran first. similary, its pointless to buy a 200K startup (first) shotgun. buy a cheaper one first, develop the feel, find whats missing and then move up to a 200K shotgun.\n\nRegards', ''),
