(37170, ' KageFox, There are two types of non resident hunters allowed in Alberta.\n\nFirst is a non resident Alien, which means someone from someplace other than Canada These hunters must be accompanied by a licensed guide and obtain non resident licenses.\n\nSecond is a Canadian resident who does not live in Alberta. Some one from Ontario for example. That person must be guided by a licensed guide or an Alberta resident with a special permit. This is so that if I had a relative or friend living elsewhere in Canada, he could come and hunt as long as I got the permit. He would also have to buy non resident licenses.\n\nI believe there are provisions for temporary residents such as students. I''ll check and see what those are.\n\nHow long are you planning to study in Ontario?', ''),
