(37211, ' [quote]\n[b]Abu Hafs wrote:[/b]\n\nThanx for the info bro,is the 590A1  model readily available in Pak? I love the idea of the DSA and would be very happy to purchase a Pak made weapon no problem,its just that when you said that the DSA doesn''t fire commercially available slugs that kind of put me off.[/quote]\n\nBrother, u said "Ideal HD weapon" and in Home defense scenario slugs are neither recommended nor advised. thats why I recommended DSA. if u want "HD+Slug Capability weapon" then in that case:\n\n1. mossberg 590A1\n2. mossberg 500\n3. maverick 88\n4. any reputable turkish pump\n\nyes! brother, Mossberg 590A1 is available in Pakistan, although very hard to find. my friend in MOF has it. awesome thing.\n\n[quote]I also  remember you saying that you were thinking of making some slugs that could be fired by the DSA, any progress on those bro?\n[/quote]\n\nstill working on it, got the slugs made, they fired totally safe in DSA pump, however their accuracy was pathetic beyond 30 yards. changed the design a bit, recently got some more slugs CNC machined with a key to better hold the shotcup. gonna fire them soon, hoping to touch the 50yrds mark with reasonable accuracy, lets see.... hopefully if it works out, molds will be made for those slugs.... its a slow process and i''m trying to get everything right before the molding/dye making process begins.\n\nRegards', ''),
(37212, ' [quote=ay_be_why]@12G, sir you are as to-the-point and helpful as always. A little more help though, i have a little confusion about the capacity of the HD shotgun. I''m of the opinion that it should have a reasonable capacity along with a size that allows easier handling (like a 5+1 being smaller than a 7+1 and having more capacity than a 3+1 DSA). But at the same time, one would like to have as much lead to pump as possible, before reloading, in an HD situation(God Forbid). What do you suggest in this regard? I hope i''ve put my point clearly...[/quote]\n\nSir, for HD, the trend is to get a shotgun with 5+1 or 7+1 capacity. to me, I like 7+1 not because it offers any significant tactical advantage over 5+1, its just my personal preference to have as much lead with me as possible. otherwise 5+1 is totally fine, keeps the weight of the gun low, increases maneuverability, but 7+1 has its own advantages, for example, i like 21-22 inch barrel for HD, as with more weight, recoil is less, muzzle blast is reduced, bang is low and usually this barrel length comes with 7+1 capacity.\n\nforget the 3+1, its for SD role only, perfect for a vehicle carry weapon. not at all recommended for HD.\n\nRegards.', ''),
