(37402, ' [quote=Enigmatic Desires]Ammo is only as good as its reliebility.. FMJs are usualy more reliable then their hollow point counterparts[/quote]\n\nnot with modern weapons.  guns that have been designed in the last few years pretty effectively feed all types of ammo.  you should try at least one magazine to be sure, but don''t need to shoot 100 (my opinion only). \n\nthe Cougar feeds everything, BTW.\n\nfor HD, keep one magazine loaded with HP (Norinco, Magtech etc) and another with FMJs.  And the shotgun near by!!!\n\nmidreestaj: you want to hit the bad guy as hard as possible, but with FMJs chances are the bullet will hit and pass through, and potentially hit some one behind...something you dont want happening.  Good HPs expand on impact and have lower penetration, dumping their energy in the target.  Obviously, premium HP (Hydrashoks, Gold Dots etc) SHOULD expand better than less high tech ones and better than FMJs.  Having said that I think an economical HP (Norinco, Magtech) is worth it if it provides some expansion vs a no expansion FMJ.', ''),
(37404, ' Asalamulekum,\nI have PA 63 makarov as a back up weapon, but small revolvers like .38 special is best to have. I think revolvers are better for back-up weapon. In case u have 2 guns jammed in a middle of a serious situation. Any how, one should be trained for pistol defence and how much cover and clearance needed prior to pulling your weapon and discharging it (most imp.) factor.\nIn a gun fight, cooler heads survive then a hot headed emotional one. \n1) shot clearance ( no innocent bystanders)\n2) If you are in a company of friends and family members.\n3) surveying how many people around you, possibly someone n the rear.\n4) cover position (dont be in open), its not wild west movie situation.\n5) number and calibers auto non auto weapons you are going to face. Pakistan has chinese made steel rounds ..keep it in mind.  \n  these are the basics and not complete, so keep this in mind when CCarrying weapon and you run into situation. Try to diffuse it by any means possible with out pulling out cc weapon. The sight of weapon camn make the morons very jittery and there not upto date spring loose triggers can chnage the whole situation against u. If they have u already in there sights, use your cool  headedness as they are always in a hurry. If they go for your weapon if visible, give it to them...dont resist, u can always live to buy another one.   Thx....Musa.', ''),
(37405, ' [quote=CougarMan]midreestaj: you want to hit the bad guy as hard as possible, but with FMJs chances are the bullet will hit and pass through, and potentially hit some one behind...something you dont want happening.  Good HPs expand on impact and have lower penetration, dumping their energy in the target.  Obviously, premium HP (Hydrashoks, Gold Dots etc) SHOULD expand better than less high tech ones and better than FMJs.  Having said that I think an economical HP (Norinco, Magtech) is worth it if it provides some expansion vs a no expansion FMJ.[/quote]\n\ndear i agree with u.. thats why i said in my post, NOT to full ur gun with FMJs.. atleast i believe in the benifits of JHP diet on a BG as compared to FMJ diet :)', ''),
