(37431, ' [quote=12gauge][quote=Turumti]Gentlemen, \n\nI went to the market today, saw all three guns - ATA, Hatsan Escort Magnum and Baikal MP153. of all these three the ATA has the best pointability, balance and feel. Next is Hatsan, followed by MP153. \n\nBoth ATA and Hatsan are supplied with 5 flush chokes, two extra O rings and stock spacers, but MP153 has only three extended chokes, that''s all, nothing else. \n\nPrice wise ATA is for around 38K, Hatsan 45K and MP153 for 53K, now please advise.\n\nRegards,[/quote]\n\nsince the MP153 is over priced and is being supplied with extended chokes instead of flush mounted, i would suggest go for Hatsan Escort. try to find a Baikal MP153 preferably 07 or 08 model with flush mounted chokes (usually supplied 3) if not, i would recommend Hatsan.\n\nRegards.\n\np.s. what do u mean by pointability?[/quote]\n\n\n@12 Gauge,\n\nBy pointability I mean the ability of a gun to come ones shoulder instantly and point right where you intend shooting at. Of course, it''s not a dog to point by itself, but if by a quirk of fate the length of pull and comb etc are all according to one''s built or even approximately so Pointability is greatly improved.\n\nWhy do you reccomend against an MP153 with extended chokes?\n\nAlso what do you think of Carlson extended chokes? Do you think they perform as well the maufacturers claim they do? Are they worth buying?\n\n[url]http://www.cabelas.com/cabelas/en/templates/links/link.jsp?type=pod&cmCat=MainCatcat602007-cat601640-cat20805&id=0003646[/url]\n\nRegards,', ''),
