(37491, ' When calling predators, you will not beat the canine nose. That is why they use dogs for sniffing drugs or explosives. \n\nAny time I set up to call coyotes, I pay close attention to the wind. I set up so I am calling into the wind. But the coyote can come from any direction, so it is important to watch my "back door" for something approaching down wind. If the coyote hits the area of my scent he will be gone as fast as he can move, and it is unlikely he will stop for a shot.\n\nMy world is not perfect and neither is the coyotes, so he makes errors. Wearing a ghillie can confuse his eyesight so even though he can get your scent, he may decide to come in for a closer look. I have no way to know how many times he has smelled a human, but I have seen them beg for food at the side of a highway rest area.\n\nWhile hunting in my ghillie, I have had coyotes come to within a meter of me from the downwind side. It can get very busy , very quickly when that happens :D\n\nCoyotes like us do not always make the correct choices in life. I have had a group of 7 coyotes come to the call. I killed one, the rest ran off. I immediately went back to my call and had the remaining six return and I killed another. I repeated this until I had 4 dead on the ground. This scene has been played for me on four different occasions. \n\nI have had bears within 3 meters and they seemed oblivious to me being there.\n\nI also use the ghillie instead of a blind while hunting ducks and geese.', ''),
