(37493, ' Interesting topic may I contribute with my following article which I printed and distributed in thousands in various schools, colleges & universities. We should inform all Muslims and discourage foreigners using such a bad name of our holly places. \n\nPlease note, the "Gora" wants his worshipping place to be called as Church but it is the height of his disregard for the other cultures that in English language he''ll use a general term like "temple" for worshipping places of other followers, whereas, the Hindu''s temple is called Mandar, the Sikhs call them Gurduwara, Muslims call them Masjid, Jews call them Synagogue and so on !  ... So !!!!\n\nIT  IS  MASJID -  NOT  MOSQUE !\n\nMany of us think that perhaps Mosque is the English translation of Masjid but in reality, it is not …! \n\nHave you ever wondered how this came into being when it does not sound anywhere close to Masjid or to be an adaptation ?\n\nMosque is a distortion of the Spanish word MOSQUITO which is used as such in English with same meaning - insect mosquito !\n\nThe word MASJID came to be termed as MOSQUE because King Ferdinard of Spain boasted that Muslims in Spain would be killed like MOSQUITOES.  The places where Muslims used to gather in large numbers were the masjids and that is where it was most convenient to attack and murder them.\n\nTo the Spaniards, taking their lead from their king, attacking congregations  of  Muslims  in  Masjids  was  indeed  like swatting mosquitoes, so the term MOSQUE (abbreviation for the place where Muslim Mosquitoes were best ''swatted''  in large numbers) was introduced.  With mosquito, as the time passed, mosque was gradually absorbed into English. \n\nMosque thus became widely used & accepted as influence of the Muslims waned and English Language spread across the world. \n\nThe Arabic word “MASJID” comes from “SAJDA” which is the right word for our prayer place. So please call it MASJID and not Mosque ! \n\nBeing a Muslim, it is now your duty to pass on this information to all other Muslim Brothers, Sisters and especially your Children !', ''),
