(37554, ' [quote=Sohail]i personally thing that O/U is with better balance i have checked both and personaly like O/U.\n\nregards[/quote]\n\nSohail bhai, balance has nothing to do with the barrel configuation, some people feel that O/U are better balanced, others feel that SxS are better balanced, in actuality, both are equally balance, its the preferance of each individual that makes him/her biased towards the "FEEL"\nof each type of shotgun.\n\nHeck, i feel my DSA pump is better balanced than any shotgun out there. in reality, I love my DSA pump, that love/admiration sorta makes me enjoy the "FEEL" of that shotgun more than it actually is.\n\nRegards', ''),
(37555, ' [quote][b]Trumuti wrote:[/b]\n\nThanks for the insight, buddy. Through which website did you order them? Were they delivered in Pakistan? Some online stores in the US do not send scope mounts and chokes etc to Pakistan[/quote]\n\nYes you are right, some will not send chokes to Pakistan, Even Cabelas will not send chokes to you given ur location [b](BEEN THERE DONE THAT)[/b], however I ordered them from Trulock, initially the company denied but after emailing the owner, Mr. George Trulock, I got his consent, i''m posting our email conversation too.\n\n****************************************************\nDear Mr. Trulock \n\nI own Baikal MP153 and IZH27 shotguns. I am also a member of a skeet club here in Pakistan. this sport is quiet new here but the word is spreading fast. \n\nAfter hearing so many good things about Trulock chokes i''ve searched everywhere in Pakistan but couldnt find any. \n\nfor simplicity i''m listing my questions: \n\n1. can you direct me to a Pakistani distributor of Trulock chokes? \n2. if not then, can I purchase them through your website? \n3. if not then, is there any other website which can deliver them to me in Pakistan? \n4. if none of the above then, is there anyway other way I can enjoy ownership/benefit/utility of Trulock chokes? \n5. if everything fails, can you advise me on how to stop dreaming about Trulock chokes mounted at the business end of my shotguns?\n\nRegards \n\np.s. i realy realy hope that it doesnt come to question 5\n\n****************************************************\nTO THIS MR. TRULOCK REPLIED\n****************************************************\nSir, \n1-We do not have a distributor in Pakistan \n2-Yes you can \nGeorge Trulock\n****************************************************\n\nI hope it helps.\n\nRegards\n\np.s. trulock is a tried and tested name, my suggestion would be to try it. if not go for colonial arms.', ''),
