(37631, ' update on hollowpoints:\nnot always a hollowpoint is gauranteed to expand, they as often as 50% clog up with material and work like a FMJ.........they over panetrate too quite often.... but expansion characteristic of this round is still far greater than a FMJ, again then choice is yours.\n\nfedral hydra shock is an old design now, they are known to clog up with material more often than newer HP types. \nworldwide GOLD DOT design is more prooven along with Winchester Ranger SXT bullet, if u want something more reliable in Federal, check HST hollowpoints. these bullet types retain much of their weight after penetration..\nretaining weight is a crucial factor to confirm full blown expansion.. hydras fragment and dont retain as much. \n3 of these HPs are new generation and recommended and do retain weight ALOT! dont clog much either:\n1- Speer Gold Dot\n2- winchester Ranger SXT - formerly Win Black Talon\n3- Corbon Power Ball\nabove 3 are real premium JHPs. If u really bet ur life on JHPs go for them.. forget these chinese/philipines/russian stuff, meanwhile ill keep aa mag of ol''time ball rounds as backup.. who knows if a ball from my barrel send the BG to hell :D', ''),
(37632, ' one thing i forgot to mention guys.. always select lighter bullets in shorter than 4" barrels.. Expansion needs velocity.. shorter barrels do not accelerate bullets to their full potency.. lighter load is recommended always even in 4inch barrels.. in 9mm 115 is ok for upto 4inch barrel. 4.5" + 124 grain is perfect..  that is why exactly 147 grain JHP even out of a 4.9 inch barrel of a 92FS over penetrate quite often..\nbut these days in 147 grain 9mm JHP m winchester Ranger ammo has made a good reputation, bullet contruction is so much improved that these rounds are able to expand to their full potential at 1000FPS and are able to penetrate better than 115 grain counter parts.\nstill a lighter load is recommended in under 4" barrel..', ''),
