(37779, ' [quote=Mohammad]Guys wanted to know about the general performance of this handgun. It share alot of similarities with the glock series pistol. I have seen couple of videos of it going through tough test without malfunction. if someone has knowledge about this handgun, please share[/quote]\n\nThey are becoming very popular in the US.\n\nI have two friends who own them and they are very happy with the gun''s design and performance.  I believe the design in almost genius.\n\nThe trigger is a bit long in it''s pull and reset, and too heavy for my tastes.  But, the trigger is not unacceptable.  I''d simply prefer a shorter, lighter trigger.\n\nGood gun, dependable, well built, smart design.  I''d give it 4 out of 5 stars and two thumbs up.', ''),
(37780, ' Welcome StevenCline on Pakguns :D', ''),
(37781, ' [quote=eminentpk]Whats your favorite CCW? and why?\nSmall calibers are easy to conceal but they are less effective\nLarge calibers are hard to conceal but they are more effective[/quote]\n\nI CCW a full-sized Kimber 1911.  It is my competition gun; I know it best, I shoot it best.  I have no problem concealling it.', ''),
(37782, ' Well...\n\nActually I came across this lovely rifle that I was after for quite some time..\n\nThe problem is.. \n\nI wanted a .308 one..\n\nThe one I have come across is its smaller sister, chambered in .222 Remington (not the 5.45 variety)\n\nI dont want to invest money in it, only to find that I''ve acquired a "safayd haathi" (white elephant)\n\nInformation on net you must be well aware is of Western origins.. and we unfortunately have different circumstances as regards weapon and particularly ammo availability..\n\nHow is it suited to target practice, and how does it hold up to our indigenous wild game?\n\nIf its just a plinker than I already have a .22\n\nAny help would be appreciated\n\nThanks', ''),
(37783, ' I have dry fired Glocks and Kimbers thousands of times with no ill effect.\n\nConcernig dry-fire:\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7mEoYHdpuLY[/url]\n\nEnjoy.', ''),
