(37795, ' Its far superior than a .22lr but not its price & availability. Its not a plinking cartridge as you are aware, its more of a varmint caliber with twice the effective range of a .22lr. Although its almost as powerful as .223 rem and will be good on small to medium game in and around 150 mtrs, in semi-auto carbines, its difficult to shoot accurately beyond 50 meters. If there is a choice, its better not to take it. Its not a proffered caliber anymore.', ''),
