(37799, ' [quote=Abu Hafs][quote=StevenCline]\n\nI CCW a full-sized Kimber 1911.  It is my competition gun; I know it best, I shoot it best.  I have no problem concealling it.[/quote]\n\n\nI can see how someone would conceal a 1911 in the winter under a overcoat for example, but how do you manage to conceal carry it when the weather is hot?[/quote]\n\nIt''s really not that difficuly my friend.  I am often in a suit.  Other times I cover with a light weight over-sized shirt.  I do use a safari vest at times.  I also make use of the carry in plain sight option by placing the gun in shoulder bag.\n\nIt''s over 80 degrees most of the year in San Antonio, TX, and over 90 or 100 for up to six months a year.\n\nHere is one of my view videos of an IDPA match shooting from concealled with a t-shirt and larger light weight covering garment:\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C4n-B3QAeOg[/url]\n\n(I was carrying a Glock 23 at the time, not a 1911)', '');
