(37810, ' [quote=StevenCline]I''ve been visiting the forums... many of the same threads could be right out of GlockTalk in the US.  Apparently gun-guys are gun-guys, no matter where they live.\n\nQuestion, if it can be asked, what is a prohibitted bore?[/quote]\n\n\nWelcome to the club steven, you are absolutely right, gun guys are gun guyz where ever they are.\n\nabout the question you asked: "prohibited bore" is a restricted weapon/caliber catagory in Pakistan. all automatic weapons, rifle calibers above .22 and assault weapons fall under this catagory.\n\nProhibited bore licenses are not for general public (next to impossible in acquisition would be more approprite) and are usually issued to VIP personnel, ministers, member national assembly, senators and heads of criticial state departments, etc. criteria wise, anybody from the general public can apply for a prohibited bore license but it would require  a pretty solid reason and strong links/contacts up the chain of bureaucracy and political establishment.\n\n\nRegards', ''),
