(37835, ' [quote=StevenCline]I''ve been visiting the forums... many of the same threads could be right out of GlockTalk in the US.  Apparently gun-guys are gun-guys, no matter where they live.\n\nQuestion, if it can be asked, what is a prohibitted bore?[/quote]\n\nWelcome aboard Steven, nice to have another member from US.\n\nProhibited & non-Prohibited bore, \n\nProhibited bore.... A gun or calibre Government of Pakistan issues license to buy/keep for under special circumstances, to special persons, for special purpose & are issued only by Federal government office. List of prohibitted bore weapons keep''s on changing depending on the country''s law & order situation. Currently all semi & auoto rifles (excluding .22 semi) & all auto weapons are in prohibitted bore list.\n\nNon-Prohibited bore.... Any Pakistan citizen can apply for this category weapon''s license to District Aministration, provincial administration or federal administration. License is issued after aplicant is verified by local police station as responsible & of a good character with no previous criminal record. As per the current list of NPB license,  we can have all semi pistol, revolver uptill .45 calibre, shotguns (restricted to semi only), .22 semi rifle, all bolt action rifles utill .45 calibre (can have a 50 bmg in any configuration ;) ).\n\nHope this answer''s your query.', ''),
