(381322, ' [QUOTE=Skeeter60;219832]Thank you \nAK 47 & Hussain Ali Sahab.\nThe Krico is made in Germany and it is a quality rifle known to be accurate and very reliable. It has two safeties, one is the cocking handle  which doubles as a bolt lock and safety and the other is a thumb safety which I personally do not like as it can be confusing and I think I will remove it after a serious thought.\nIt is very accurate for a semi auto but no where near the Anshutz or the good old Brno. I will post pictures and my impressions of the rifle. The Anshutz 1913 s are capable of one hole ten shot groups at 50m with good ammo like the 10 X etc and the Brno can shoot 1/2 inch 5 shot groups with a Ziess Pecar scope and the Anshutz 1416 makes .20 to .25 inch 5 shot  groups at 50 m with a Schmidt & Bender 6 X Scope .[B] I expect the Krico to shoot about 1/2 to 3/4 inch groups with good ammo at 50 m.[/B] Will put it through the paces soon.[/QUOTE]\n\nThanks Skeeter Sir for the preliminary introduction above.\n\nI trust the 1/2-3/4 inch grouping at 50 mtrs with the Krico is still more than sufficient for small game hunting, your technical observations and comparisons with the other ones being more [I]competition specific[/I], I suppose?\n\nIn any case, looking forward to seeing the beauty itself, specifically because I was intending a 30K air-gun sooner or later, so if at 40K one good have a reasonably good make NIB .22, why not? Though, course, air-gunning is a whole different pleasure, but heck, the .22 is no less, lolz!\n\n\nSir, was it wooden or plastic?\n\n\nRegards.', ''),
