(38017, ' [quote=Turumti]@12 Gauge, \n\nSaeen, please tell us what all we shoyuld expect to receive with a brand new in the box, Baikal MP153. Here in Karachi all these MP153''s have nothing more thn what Cap 1 mentioned. Do you think these dealers are pulling a fast one on us?\n\nYour input will be greatly appreciated.[/quote]\n\n\nRegular boxed MP153 usually has three to four chokes, a choke wrench, a manual and a magazine plug installed in the tube(limits the magazine capacity to two shots only). very few and quiet rare ones can even have 5 chokes. This is the standard available stuff.\n\nhowever occassionally, there is a special model called "Practical Shooting" model. its standard baikal mp153 by all means, just provided with loads of accessories such as: fiber optic sights, extra magazine spring, extra recoil spring, buttstock spacers (to increase the LOP) and supplied with seven chokes, (four flush, three extended for steel shot) and a cheap plastic trigger lock (i''m guessing by the remains of it)\n\nRegards\n\np.s. If i were to buy by Baikal MP153 again, I would go for a regular model as Practical shooting model is highly over priced and usually supplied with accessories that are either broken, bent or sub-standard (factory fiber optic bead sucks, too small to collect and channel any light) and do nothing but collect dirt. or may be the one i got was tossed around too much during shipping :(', ''),
