(38045, ' [quote=Moeen]@ Abu Hafs - ASTM is the international standard for treated metals.  The number besides it designates what or how much of what content is mixed and at what temp. was the metal heat treated for example: 4140 as used by most in US firearms industry is rated at 50 to 55 hrc which is heat treatment for hardness.  Remember the harder the metal the less it tends to bend and rather breaks or becomes brittle.  \nIn Aluminum the number is almost always designated with a T.... for example M16 are made using T7075, to some manufacturers are using T6.\n\nAnd yes as stated by you and by me - everything OEM except frame.  Its harder than the Glock frame due to the fact that I used PA66/gf10 (Nylon 6 with 10% glass fiber mix).[/quote]\n\n\nWOW, Thank you Moeen bhai this is one awesome operation you got going on there MasahaAllah may ALLAH grant you further success.\n\n\nBro, how will I know Im  getting one of your quality products? Is anyone else producing cheap imitations in Darra or are all Glock clones made in your factory?  Do you have a specific dealer in Darra that is the main retailer of your products?', ''),
