(38065, ' According to the author of the above article that I have posted the best standard 9mm rounds i.e standard meaning non +P rounds are \n\n[quote]\nThe best standard pressure 9mm load is the Federal 115 grain JHP (9BP). Its effectiveness and accuracy make it the world standard. Buy several boxes. Other excellent standard pressure 9mm loads are the Winchester Silvertip 115 grain (X9MMSHP), and Federal 124 grain Hydra-shok (P9HS1).[/quote]\n\n\nSo my question is, are any of the above named 9mm rounds readily available in the gun stores in Peshawar or Islamabad?\n\n\nIn the .357 caliber he recommends \n\n\n[quote]The most effective handgun round on the market - regardless of caliber - is the Federal .357 Magnum 125 grain jacketed hollowpoint (357B). This load has more stopping power than any other handgun bullet (and this includes more powerful rounds like the .41 and .44 Magnums). I advise all experienced revolver men to carry the legendary Federal 357B in a .357 revolver, or the equally good Remington full-power 125 grain semi-jacketed hollowpoint (R357M1).[/quote]\n\nWhats the availability of these rounds like?\n\n\nThanks for your feed back', ''),
