(38074, ' [quote=midreestaj]one thing i forgot to mention guys.. always select lighter bullets in shorter than 4" barrels.. Expansion needs velocity.. shorter barrels do not accelerate bullets to their full potency.. lighter load is recommended always even in 4inch barrels.. in 9mm 115 is ok for upto 4inch barrel. 4.5" + 124 grain is perfect..  that is why exactly 147 grain JHP even out of a 4.9 inch barrel of a 92FS over penetrate quite often..\nbut these days in 147 grain 9mm JHP m winchester Ranger ammo has made a good reputation, bullet contruction is so much improved that these rounds are able to expand to their full potential at 1000FPS and are able to penetrate better than 115 grain counter parts.\nstill a lighter load is recommended in under 4" barrel..[/quote]\n\n\nExcellent info bro,\n\nAre all the rounds you named widely available or would one have o hunt far and wide to get ones hands on them?\n\nAlso is the weight of the rounds i.e the[b] grains[/b] labeled on the ammo pack?', ''),
