(38085, ' [quote=Starfish]9mm (since 12g is not an option)[/quote]\n\nhey! hey! hey!, i saw that :mad:\n\nAllow me to compare the impotent 9mm round with the macho 12gauge 00 buckshot (commonly called SG here)\n\n[b]9MM ballistics (typical):[/b]\n\nBullet weight: 115gr or 7.45 grams\nBullet diameter: .36inch\nEnergy: 367 ft/lb\nMomentum: 19.71\nVelocity: 1200 FPS\n\n[b]12 gauge 00 buck shot or SG ballistics (typical):[/b]\n\nNo. of Pellets: 9\nDiameter of each Pellet: .33inch\nweight of each pellet: 54gr\ntotal weight of all 9 pellets: 486gr or 31.5 grams\nVelocity of each Pellet: 1140 FPS\nOverall Energy: 1402 ft/lb\nOverall Momentum: 79.14\n\n[b]Conclusion:[/b]\n\nif 9mm hand gun round kills then 12 gauge 00 buck shot makes sure that u be the only guy in heaven walking around with 9 holes in ur chest.\n\nRegards\n\np.s. I know that one can get better ballistics from a 9mm +p round but a 12gauge 00 magnum can open a whole new can of whoopass. anothing thing: one might think of 9mm hollow points for better results but a 12gauge slug will put in you in a serious hurt locker and slam the door shut.', ''),
