(38184, ' @Abu Hafs\nAs already mentioned by othe rmembers you only need to send one CNIC copy and two Passport Size Photograph and that is the end of that. If you go into legal procedures then there are many which cannot be fulfilled. When you get the License there is a time limit of Three Months for Purchase of weapon and it can be increased if expired but its agian a hectic job. If you ask one of your relatives to purchase in your absence, that can also be done only if you have good relations with the Arms Dealer. I personally over did my Three Months Limit and after that it took me On Month to get another Month''s Limit. If you apply for MOI from Punjab, me or any other expert member will be happy to guide your relative in the whole procedure. You just need good relations with the dealer as i have twice now sent only License to the dealer and he sent me the weapon himself after getting it cleared from the agent after weapon purchase.\nHopefully i cleared everything up so now please ask such questions in a different Topic or contact me personally as this is not the right Topic for it.', ''),
(38185, ' A quick warning before you go with night sights. They will show through summer-weight clothing when it is dark out. With the half-life of tritium, you’re looking at about two years before they dim enough to not do that any more. However, they also won’t be as visible by then either.\nThere is another option offer by Glock the Glock Night Sights and these are guaranteed for life by Glock.\nThere is another option which you can try just for free :) get some glow-in-the-dark nail polish and apply to the factory sights with a toothpick… You just gotta make sure your gun sits out in the daylight for a little while every couple of hours.\nYou should try Harris if you are in Karachi as he told something about having Trijicon Night Sights. He can also import it for you.', ''),
(38186, ' I presume you have used Tritium sights ?', ''),
(38187, ' Beautifuly Engraved TT.\nWeapon instead of Beautiful Girl, i will reserve my comments on that  :)', ''),
(38188, ' before doing any thing with your weapon 1st find out how they will replace the rear sight do they have proper tool, because i think removing rear sight is quite a difficult task. Adeel''s night glow nailpolish is good idea, but do not apply directly on the sight just take a good adhesive sticker and paint 3 coates of nailpolish and cut it nicely just as the same size of sight out line like a strip and then stick it over. even i will rty this, kiya harj hai experiement kar ne mein.', ''),
(38189, ' First Tritium has a half life of 12 years, so they will be half as bright after twelve years but still useable.\n\nI have access to the tools needed to install them. BTW its always the front sights which are difficult to install.  \n\nGlow in dark does not cut it for me', ''),
(38190, ' bro you just remove the slide and you can see the screw, but rear sight yo have to pull it from the top i think, if some on can define it would nice to know for my knowledge.', ''),
(38191, ' First of all the choices given are all for Hand Guns, hence no Shot Gun can be included in that. If the scenario is that you are in a self defense situation at home, i would prefer a Shot Gun as none of us are Trained Tactical Shooters who shot someone by just looking at the reflection in mirror. (Angelina Jolie In Wanted) You have to be extremely accustomed with your weapon to fully utilize it in an SD/HD situation as most of the time Panic kicks in and while using a .45 ACP or 9MM, we might be empty before we even hit the culprit. Its not just about killing the person but actually saving yourself and your family at that time. If we go into detail of using any Calibre other then 9MM, then its extremely expensive at the end of the day. We might have to fire at least 500 Rounds to just get accurate enough to shoot something at the first try. I feel that there is still room for error in that. It does not depend on the calibre you are using but how you are going to use it without panicking at all.', ''),
