(38360, ' The primary aim while selecting a ammo is to kill or injure a person. We people are too much impressed with American society. The results of killing an indl (that is 302) is much different then injuring a person. Human life is too precious to be wasted like this. I think that small bullets like 32 bore or even .22 are very effective in stopping anyone with less chances of killing and then facing the sweat music of our judicial /police system.\nBullets like hallow point and buck shots are very lethal and should not be used at all except by security forces.', ''),
(38361, ' Problem is, smaller bullets like those aforementioned have lower energy upon impact. The aim of selecting the correct ammo is not to kill, not to injure. It is to simply STOP, whichever way possible. Now the smaller (and faster) calibers do create wounds, but due to lower energy at impact time (or simply zipping through the body tissue, due to higher velocities), they are unable to stop the assailant in time. Agreed that all of them can kill, maim, injure, etc, but some of them have a higher probability of stopping an assailant than others due to the fact that they deliver higher impact energy, thus the word "stopping power".\n\nThe objective of someone in an SD situation is to simply stop the assailant as quickly as possible. Granted that the smaller calibers can stop the fight, but the more powerful ones may be able to stop it in one go.\n\nBtw, the best caliber for SD/HD in handguns would preferably be the .45ACP or the .357 Magnum, but due to the higher recoil of these rounds, the 9mm, .38 Special and the .40 S&W (where it''s available) are more than enough.\n\nAs far as only [b]HD[/b] is concerned, the best bet would be a 12 Gauge shotgun. I''m not generally in favor of .22 semi auto rifles for home defence.', ''),
