(38386, ' Steven, Its nice to know your interest in PAKISTAN scene. Let me summarize few things which can enable you to understand the overall scenario.\n1. GUNS are very expensive here, especially premium products like GLOCKS etc. A GLOCK 17 costs around $4000 here. This makes the ownership a very exclusive affair. Thats why Chinese 7.62 (.30 calibre) handguns & 9mm s are the most common. A chinese SIG clone costs around $500 in the local market.\n2. Ammo is also very expensive. 9mm chinese ammo costs around $45 per 100 rounds. That also makes things a lot on the up side considering our per capita income.\n3. Ranges & clubs are very few. You can say only 3 in whole of PAKISTAN. \nDespite all this GUNS are a very traditional things here. They are regarded are a MAN''s JEWELLERY. Lot of enthusiasts here prefer it over owning a nice car etc etc. Also in certain TRIBAL & remote areas where you can see a lot of guns , you will be amazed at the shooting skills the people can display. In my opinion its always the passion which counts above esay access or availablity, otherwise similar countries like ours in SOUTH AMERICA would not have been producing so much classy soccer players', ''),
