(38559, ' a taurus wouldn''t really do the trick for you, if you are looking for some thing cheap i would advise you go for an NP 42 but if you have a sober budget go for a glock 17 C. \n\nGLOCK pistols have three independent and automatic safeties. As the trigger is pulled they sequentially disengage, and as the pistol fires and the trigger returns to its forward position, they re-engage. The combination of the trigger safety, firing pin safety and drop safety make the GLOCK the safest pistol on the market , that''s the most nicest thing you can do.\n\nWithin the price range of 80 K and above try and see whether you can get a sigma S&W but i heard they were not really on the proper import lists and the only ones sold were the smuggled ones. but in my personal opinion', ''),
