(38632, ' Warning shots are the best if you notice burglars outside the vicinity of your home. They will serve to drive away the bad guys.\n\n\nHowever, if your house has been invaded and the BD(s) are inside, then you have to be the one to take the initiative. They are threatening you on your turf, and if you don''t do something about it, some loved one might get injured or GOD FORBID, killed.\n\nGoing through this topic, I am reminded of a passage in a fiction story I read long ago. A young boy questions an elderly cop (or cowboy) how has he survived for so long, seeing as he doesn''t have particularly impressive skills. The old man answered: my opponents hesitated, and I didn''t.\n\nIMHO if someone is inside your house, threatening you or your family, stay safe. Shoot first.\n\nIf someone says I don''t know what I''m talking about, let me just say that I''ve been a victim of a holdup at gunpoint inside my own house. The experience is quite scary to share, as I was quite young at the time (around 11), but let me tell you this: If I can help it, I will never let myself or a loved one go through that experience again.', ''),
