(38669, ' Unfortunately Taurus PT-92/99 is a bit large for concealed carry; its a great gun. If I were carrying cocked and locked, the pistols to consider would be: Taurus 917 (still a little large), Taurus 909, Taurus 915, NP-42 (or CF-98) or a CZ clone (Chinese NZ-75, Sarsilmaz B6/B6C). I''m  really not sure if the stoeger cougar can be carried cocked and locked. Maybe one of our senior members can shed light on this.\n\nCheck out the specs of your considered weapon carefully. If possible try to get feel for them, and in the end, get something which is reliable and suits your hand well.\n\n@Sniper: Dear Sir, all Taurus pistols are NOT unreliable. If you categorize the polymer series (24/7, Millennium) as such, then I might agree. However the steel-bodied PT92/99 are one of the most reliable pistols, and their different variants follow suit. I suggest a simple rule for people going for Taurus: Polymer: Be careful, Steel: Go Ahead!', ''),
