(38845, ' [quote=Ahmad][quote=Enigmatic Desires]A variant of the desi Pashpasha \n\n A must have in the arsenal of all shot gun lovers.\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tnrizaO-X00&NR=1[/url][/quote]\n\n@ ED  Although they are very common here as they were made in millions but Pashpasha is not a desi gun, if by this term you mean PPSH-41 sub machine gun, &  then AA shot gun is not a variant of PPSh. they share their feeding system as both use drum magazines but i am afraid resemblance ends here.\n PPSH is a blow back action which fires from open bolt like many other SMGs. AA shot gun is a Locked breach Gas operated shot gun. \nHTH[/quote]\n\n\nOh No, not at all. \n\nThe PPSH was the standard SMG of the Red army during the "gr8 patriotic war" ( as the soviets referred to the 2nd world war) \n\nThe pash pasha is a variant of the south African ''street sweeper'' design of shot guns pioneered in the late 80s to combat urban gurrila war fare', ''),
