(39073, ' [quote=KageFox]Discussing lethality, I came across some info yesterday. Normally you have different sized ball bearings in shells, or you have solid slugs. There is also a special purpose shotgun shell loaded with flechetes (needle-like ammo). Only in use by secret special forces, though its usage is banned by the Geneva Convention or something similar.\n\nFor more info on flechetes, search for "shotgun" on [url]www.howstuffworks.com[/url][/quote]\n\n\nThere are oodles of rounds for the shot gun. from party favour rounds that go off with a bang and an shower people with confetti to rubber non lethal ones. to dragon''s breath rounds that turn a shot gun into a flame thrower.. . \n\nThere are literally dozens an dozens of different rounds around..', ''),
(39075, ' Its called TIMEX and it says the hands on a clock are placed at ten-ten because it''s a creative standard industry.\n\nTimex says the hands on timepieces are placed at ten-ten so the company logo on the face will be framed and not blocked by the hands.\n\nTimex says the industry standard used to be eight-twenty but that looked too much like a frown and created an unhappy look.\n\nTimex says in its ads, the clock hands are placed at ten-nine and thirty six seconds, exactly."', ''),
