(39504, ' [quote=MHMalik][quote=Starfish]Malik SB, Awesome weapons!!\nI am seriously planning to buy the benelli... Any shortcommings i should be aware of?\nthanks,[/quote]\n\nSir \n\nThe only "reviewable" experience I have with benellis is with this one only and the M2Super 90.. and I have no complaints.. issues whatsoever with it.\n\nHowever the M1014 is an offensive weapon.. I believe it is called a combat shotgun rather than a defender.. and is built to take the highest powered loads.. In its testing it was required to fire 25000 rounds without cleaning and parts replacement which it did with flying colors...\n\nBut you should be aware that it is a bit on the heavier side.\n\nIt is great for room clearing/breaching operations.. and with slugs will become a full powered rifle at distances upto 80+ metres.. It has rifle type ghost ring night sights as well.\n\nIf you want somewhat comparable performance in a lightweight package may I suggest the Benelli M2 Super90 with Comfortech stock (mind you though the M2 is inertia driven so may not particularly like local birdshot. but is a sweet shooting gun)\n\nIf on the other hand low power loads are a requirement, The Benelli M3 would be more suitable as it is both pump action and can operate in semi auto mode as well depending on your particular requirement..[/quote]\n\nThank you Malik sb, for taking the time and effort to provide a detailed answer to my question.\nI have examined both the M3 and the M4 and so far I have found the M4 to be a much better weapon than the M3, and yes I  did notice the barrel heavy nature of the M4 the moment I held it in my hand. Thanks for pointing it out.\nThe fore and foremost reason I plan to buy the M4 is because i like it so much :) and that its a good weapon. Baqi I think it is also an excellent repeater and falls into a weapon category which i currently don''t have. A dependable, reliable, short stocked repeater which can cycle ammo reliably and fire slugs as well.\nI think M4 fits just fine :d\nI think I am going to get it soon :P\n\nThank you again for your advice. Really appreciate it.', ''),
