(39848, ' [quote=Dr Zakir]i would like the input of fellow pakgunners about their opinion for best calibre for HD / SD , 9mm , .45 ,.357 mag , .40 , 10 mm, .30 , .357 sig . \nalso kindly check the link [url=http://www.freerepublic.com/focus/news/849728/posts]www.freerepublic.com/focus/news/849728/posts[/url][/quote]\n\nLike others I subscribe to a pragmatic belief that almost anything will suffice if you shoot well.  Any caliber between 9mm/.38/.357 to .45 acp.\n\nWe should recall that the American mafia made lots of kills with the .22 magnum.\n\nLots of people have been killed with 9mm and .45, and now lots with .40 S&W. \n\nSince one can''t line up 10,000 people and shot 1000 each with the ten most popular self-defense calibers, all opinons are valid and remain simply argumentative.  We can''t control for shot placement, drug use, will to live, size disparity and a whole lot of other factors in studies of police shooting studies in the US.\n\nI tend to agree with the FBI which opined that a deep driving bullet (at least 12" in balistic gelatin) is more important that bullet size, and second, the bigger the better.\n\nSince almost all modern handgun cartridges will get you 12" of penetration \n\n[img]http://img6.imageshack.us/img6/973/handgungelcomparison.jpg[/img]\n\nand all almost all expand about as reliably as the next... \n[img]http://img6.imageshack.us/img6/2711/handgunexpandedjhp.jpg[/img]\n\nit''s really kinda moot.\n\nJust have a gun and know how to shoot it well.\n[img]http://img6.imageshack.us/img6/95/jitcrunchaspx.jpg[/img]\n\nPlease, no one take my post as insulting or disparaging.  I am only sharing my opinion.  No one has scientifically proven their opinon on this correct and neither can I prove my opinion correct.\n\nThat being said we use 1911 in .45 around the house and my wife carries a 9mm Kahr concealed outside the house.', ''),
(39849, ' [quote=Abu Hafs][quote=CougarMan]the best calibre is the one that you have in your hand at that moment!!![/quote]\n\n\nYes but which one are you going to make sure is in your hand if and when needed?[/quote]\n\nFor me it is my Kimber 1911 in .45.  Just one man''s choice.  It is not proof of it''s superiority.', ''),
