(39852, ' [quote=12gauge][quote=Starfish]9mm (since 12g is not an option)[/quote]\n\nhey! hey! hey!, i saw that :mad:\n\nAllow me to compare the impotent 9mm round with the macho 12gauge 00 buckshot (commonly called SG here)\n\n[b]9MM ballistics (typical):[/b]\n\nBullet weight: 115gr or 7.45 grams\nBullet diameter: .36inch\nEnergy: 367 ft/lb\nMomentum: 19.71\nVelocity: 1200 FPS\n\n[b]12 gauge 00 buck shot or SG ballistics (typical):[/b]\n\nNo. of Pellets: 9\nDiameter of each Pellet: .33inch\nweight of each pellet: 54gr\ntotal weight of all 9 pellets: 486gr or 31.5 grams\nVelocity of each Pellet: 1140 FPS\nOverall Energy: 1402 ft/lb\nOverall Momentum: 79.14\n\n[b]Conclusion:[/b]\n\nif 9mm hand gun round kills then 12 gauge 00 buck shot makes sure that u be the only guy in heaven walking around with 9 holes in ur chest.\n\nRegards\n\np.s. I know that one can get better ballistics from a 9mm +p round but a 12gauge 00 magnum can open a whole new can of whoopass. anothing thing: one might think of 9mm hollow points for better results but a 12gauge slug will put in you in a serious hurt locker and slam the door shut.[/quote]\n\nThis is true, one police instructor I knew (he trained me) likened to getting hit once with 00 12 gauge to getting hit 9 times with a 9mm.  May not be complete accurate, but it is very close.\n\nFew people live through a single shotgun blast.', ''),
(39855, 'Opinion on Short Barreled Shotguns for HD/SD I saw some vids on Ytube of shotguns with 14 inch barrels.One was a Remington model "1187 Police".\n\nThere was also other short  models made by Norinco. I really liked the look of  these, very tactical for use in car etc and could even be concealed if stock is removed and pistol grip is used.\n\nAnyway gentlemen what do you think of these short barreled shotguns as far as use as a defensive weapon is concerned?\n\nWhat is the availability of these in Pakistan? Have you seen any in the gun stores? \n\nDo they come with fixed barrels or can you have short and long interchangeable barrels.\n\n\nAll info welcome please,   price, availability, recommend or not etc etc \n\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_wemLXwBGhY&feature=related[/url]\n\n\nThis video states "Norinco Remington 870", does this mean that this is a Norinco clone of a 870 with a short barrel?\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ul1QDc19veM[/url]\n\nThanks', ''),
