(40081, ' [quote=Abu Hafs]I saw some vids on Ytube of shotguns with 14 inch barrels.One was a Remington model "1187 Police".\n\nThere was also other short  models made by Norinco. I really liked the look of  these, very tactical for use in car etc and could even be concealed if stock is removed and pistol grip is used.\n\nAnyway gentlemen what do you think of these short barreled shotguns as far as use as a defensive weapon is concerned?\n\nWhat is the availability of these in Pakistan? Have you seen any in the gun stores? \n\nDo they come with fixed barrels or can you have short and long interchangeable barrels.\n\n\nAll info welcome please,   price, availability, recommend or not etc etc \n\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_wemLXwBGhY&feature=related[/url]\n\n\nThis video states "Norinco Remington 870", does this mean that this is a Norinco clone of a 870 with a short barrel?\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ul1QDc19veM[/url]\n\nThanks[/quote]\n\n\nAoA brother.\n\nhmm.... a 14 inch barrel shotgun, pretty common configuration for a car carry weapon, infact mostly used by VIP security detail. Here is Pakistan, shotguns with 14 inch barrels are quiet common but elsewhere in the developed world usually such shotguns are restricted as their barrel size is shorter than 18 inches.\n\nhere, i''ve seen, mossy, DSA  and remington pumps with 14 inch barrels. they are called cruiser models (no need to explain why ofcourse). I''ve used DSA pump with 14 inch barrels. same standard receiver, same pistol grip, shorter forend, shorter barrel (ofcourse), cylinder bore (otherwise DSA usually makes modified choked barrels).\n\nallow me to explain what i felt after firing a couple of cartridges at the DSA factory in Peshawar.\n\n1. muzzle blast is absolutely horrible (looks like a dragon spitting a huge ball of fire)\n2. loud bang/noise (perfect if u want to lose ur hearing ability before u hit 40)\n3. pattern, well, its cylinder bore on a 14 inch barrel, so what can u expect, its pretty wide for a shotgun. keep in mind that this is the exact plan here.\n4. stout recoil, shorter barrel reduces the weight, hence unable to soak up recoil.\n\nin my experience, as a car carry weapon, weilded by a designated person, its spot on perfect. but for the driver its not. cause a driver cannot hold the weapon and drive at the same time. for that purpose, i would suggest a pistol. the weapon though alot smaller than a regular shotgun, is still quiet large for a car carrry weapon (specially for the driver). large weapons are the slowest to draw, when anticipating a fire fight. one more thing, the limited magazine capacity is such a turn off.\n\nSummary:\n\nfor car carry, its fine as long as u get somebody else to hold it. but for the driver alone to handle such a thing and drive at the same time. its quiet useless IMHO.\n\nRegards.', ''),
