(40173, ' Abbas bhai i have  air rifles of three calibers and i think they are the only calibers for air guns which includes .177, .20, and .22 caliber.\n.177 is the most famous one in air rifles and its pellets are the smallest of the 3 calibers. It can be fired at the highest velocities for given amount of airgun energy which results in the flattest trajectory.If the main purpose of your air rifle is going to be target shooting then choosing a .177 cal air rifle is a smart choice. .177 air rifles shoot around 1000 FPS and at this velocity one easily kill small squirrels, birds and other small rodents.', ''),
(40174, ' I havent seen any air rifle of .20 caliber in Pakistan and it think its rare caliber. The .20 cal pellets in of 5mm in size and has a greater energy than .177.A .20 cal pellet depending on the rifle used is effective up to about 60 yards. With a good pellet you might be able to increase that by a few yards. I have a Sheridan pump style air rifle in a .20 cal and soon post the pics.', ''),
