(40192, ' As far as I know, the air gun calibers are:\n\n.177 (4.5mm) (aka No. 1 pellets)\n.20 (5mm)\n.22 (5.5mm) (aka No. 2 pellets)\n.25 (aka No. 3 pellets)\n.35 (9mm)\n.45\n.50\n\nThe latter 3 calibers are only available in high-power PCPs (Pre-Charged Pneumatics), which are usually expensive affairs. \n\nFor more info on selecting air gun calibers, visit [url]http://www.pyramydair.com/site/articles/calibers/[/url]\n\nMy personal favorite: the .22, as it is (in my eyes) the perfect blend between power and accuracy, as well as velocity. Remember, high velocity pellets are not always good, and may tumble in mid-air, resulting in bad accuracy (eg. Gamo Raptor)', ''),
