(40347, ' Salams,\n\nRecently the most unplanned of GTG''s happened and it was perhaps the best one yet. \n\nI got a call while I was in Murree a few days back and found out that Imu10 and Taurus were in Lahore for the night, Sohail was also flying in the next day. I told Ka_Khan who wanted to meet them all so we decided to meet midway, my Village !\n\nI will post quite a few pictures and let them do all the talking, the ''gang'' will fill you in on the rest. InshAllah someday I plan to have a proper larger PakGuns GTG there, although invitees will only be from senior members and above and expert panel members . \n\n[b]I also have another announcement to make, Taimur will be stepping down as mod at his request and Taurus has reconsidered my request to become mod at PakGuns[/b]. Wish you both the best.\n\nNote: Some pictures contain P.B weapons as they were part of our GTG and are licensed in my own name. The status/rules for our forums remains the same otherwise. This is a one off exception.  \n\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip1.jpg[/img]\n\n\nChilling out after a long journey. (From Left to Right: Sohail, Taurus, Abbas, Imu10, Ka_Khan)\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip2.jpg[/img]\n\n\nAppetizer ;)\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip3.jpg[/img]\n\n\nAbbas thinking "Crap, will 2500 rounds be enough for a five hours shootout session?"\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip4.jpg[/img]\n\n\nMe and Kamran sighting in the target area while Sohail and Taurus chilling out\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip5.jpg[/img]\n\n\nOur Mod from Peshawar: Kamran Khan\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip6.jpg[/img]\n\n\nOur new Mod from Karachi packing a AR-15: Taurus\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip7.jpg[/img]\n\n\nSohail getting a taste of the AR.\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip8.jpg[/img]\n\n\nA part of the Midnight barbecue feast (We requested to have it all made the desi way)\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip9.jpg[/img]\n\n\nAt the Havelli\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip10.jpg[/img]\n\n\nResting among Olive trees after a Shooting Session\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip11.jpg[/img]\n\n\nGrapes & Olives (I love my area and rate it among one of the most beautiful in Pakistan)\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip12.jpg[/img]\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip13.jpg[/img]\n\n\nThe boys strike a pose. \n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip14.jpg[/img]\n\n\nNatural beauty in the heart of Punjab\n\n[img]http://i262.photobucket.com/albums/ii99/AbbasMalik/Trip15.jpg[/img]', ''),
