(40382, ' The magazine is, a lot of the time, responsible for the malfunctions in a gun. Even today, after more than two decades, the US Army uses only magazines from 2 manufacturers in their Beretta M9: Beretta themselves, and Mec-Gar. All other third-party magazines have, more or less, failed.\n\nA good magazine is equal to a good gun. Without the magazine, the gun cannot feed. Without the gun, bullets in a magazine cannot fire. Its the combined working of both which makes the gun shoot well.\n\nKeep up the good work, Moeen Bhai. All in good time...', ''),
