(40422, ' [quote=PakistanGuides][quote=Starfish][quote=PakistanGuides]I wish I could take all my friends at Pak Guns to Concordia but the problem is it is very expensive .. even if we rough it out with daal roti .. the main expense is of porters which always makes the trek very expensive.\n\nUnfortunately, the porters always prefer to go with the climbing expeditions because they can go fast with them, drop their baggage at the base camp & with no baggage on their backs they run back quickly to catch another one, whereas, with a trekking party they have to go slow and walk every day (in & out) and carry the loads till the end so they dont like this and usually overcharge or creat problems with trekkers. To avoid problems, we over pay them but only when we have foreigners with us but in case of poor Pakistanis ... they show no mercy ... ! All other items of the treks are managable ! \n\nI''m lucky to have been to Concordia over six times while escorting with my treks & expeditions but I can''t forget my solo trek which I did in Oct 88 with 01 cook & 6 porters and this is was the firs time I carried no weight on my back. Even my camera was carried by one of my porters so I really enjoyed and made lots of photos. \nIn 1988, this solo trek costed me Rs 165,000/=  .. but its duration was quite long ![/quote]\n\n:o qaiser sb, the cost is too much. in 2004, it cost 25k per person for a group of 7 ppl to go including the porters food equipment and all and travel from lahore... some equipment was provided by our adventure club but still.\ni dont know how your cost was so high.[/quote]\n\nDear Starfish,\nMy treking cost to concordia was high because i went there in October when the snow was waist deep .. so obviously, the porters charged me winter wages which are two to three times more plus I had to give them complete winter cloting from head to toe including jackets, boots, sleeping bags, tents + all other items you normally give them in summer treks. \nSecondly, my trip was very long all the way from Dasu to Concorda, K2 base camp & back then to the base camps of G1 & G2 and then up to Convoy Saddle, Left Thumb, Laghari Post ... etc. and as you know the porters charge you according to stages and not as per the actual days so the total number of stages to all these camps costed me lot of money. And last but not the least, since I was alone, it costed me more because I had to carry the same camping & kitchen gear which a group of 4 to 6 people need ... the only increase is the number of plates and spoons !!! so if I had 4 to 6 more people in my group it would have costed me the same amount ! .. hope this is clear now ![/quote]\n\n\nYeah it is. thanks a lot :)\n\nGuys, a group of friends is going to snowlake in a week. The trek will be of 22 days including travel and rest at hunza at the end.\ncost is around 30k all inclusive. (subsidized by the adventure society adn some kind kind sponsors )\nwe start from dassu askole, and hop on to biafoo glacier, from traversing the glacier will lead us finally to snowlake. camp for a day at snow lake and then take the hisper la (hisper pass) and come down via the hisper glacier and off to hunza. a weeks rest in hunza then :P\nPorters will be provided for communal weight.\nmajority equipment will be provided. you will need to get a backpack. sleeping bag and some warm clothes yourself. oh and your  shoes as well:P\n\nPlease be advised that you will need to be fit, and carry approx 18 kgs of weight on your back (or whatever you decide to bring).\nWe have 3 seats on the squad available so far. 9 ppl have already signed up including 2 foreigners. let me know if you guys are interested.\nYou will be briefly interviewed / screened for physical fitness before you can join in :)', ''),
